title: herbed olive cheese log
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Chill until firm enough to handle.
Shape into logs and roll in parsley flakes.
Chill.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Sprinkle apple chunks with first cinnamon and sugar mixture. Combine all other ingredients in order given and beat to make a smooth batter.
Pour half of batter into greased Turks head or angel cake pan.
(A Bundt pan may also be used.)
Arrange half apples over batter.
Top with remaining batter and then remaining apples.
Spread evenly over top.
Bake 1 1/4 hours or until cake is golden brown at 350°.
Turn out of pan carefully and let stand to cool on rack.

title: s'mores
directions: Place marshmallows and chocolate on top of graham cracker. Place another graham cracker on top if needed.

title: spicy chocolate bars
directions: Mix in big bowl the shortening, sugar, brown sugar and eggs. Add remaining ingredients and mix. Put into ungreased pan. Bake 20 minutes at 325°. Cool; cut into bars.

title: wreath christmas cookies
directions: Melt butter on low heat.
Add marshmallows and melt.
Add food coloring and stir in corn flakes.
Spoon onto buttered waxed paper.
Place cinnamon candies (2) in the middle of each cookie.

title: elegant mashed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook potatoes.
Mash or whip with warm milk and butter to make mashed potatoes. Fold in the eggs, sour cream and cottage cheese.
Mix well. Add the green onions.
Place in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
Roll out/crush enough Cheese Nips crackers to completely cover the potatoes.
Drizzle with melted butter or margarine. Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until hot.
Serves 10.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage up.
Fry beef until lightly browned; drain well. In a 3-quart casserole dish, place 1/3 of coarsely cut cabbage, top with 1/2 of beef and 1/2 onion.
Top with 1/3 cabbage, then rest of beef and onion.
Then finish with cabbage.
Pour can of soup on the top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Measure sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Heat until boiling, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; stir well.
Add cereal and mix.
Pack firmly into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips.
Spread over cereal mixture.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine eggs, butter and powdered sugar.
Beat on high for 10 minutes and pour into crust.
Layer bananas (sliced) and pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make chocolate cake. Bake in oven. Make pudding and put in refrigerator. Chill cake in refrigerator. Cut cake into 2 x 2 squares.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to ground beef and onion.
Simmer about 20 minutes.

title: flounder rolls with lemon-carrot filling
directions: Coat a skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add carrots and green onions.
Saute until crisp-tender.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and next 5 ingredients; stir well.
Set aside.

title: aroz saudi(fragrant saudi rice)
directions: Melt butter and brown meat evenly on all sides. Add cloves, cinnamon, salt, pepper and ground cardamom to meat and stir-fry about 10 minutes. Pour three cups boiling water over meat and cover.
Let cook for one hour on a medium-high heat, until meat is done.
Measure the broth left in a measuring cup. Add water to have a total of 3-1/2 cups liquid.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in oblong baking dish.
Mix the eggs, milk, 1 stick oleo, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla together. Pour over the potatoes.
Mix the brown sugar, flour, 1/2 stick melted oleo and pecans together and pour over the top of the dish.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry molded salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add sugar and juices.
Stir and chill until partially set.
Add remaining ingredients and let set. Nuts may be sprinkled on top.
Serves 12.

title: yum yum pineapple salad(a favorite at holiday time.)
directions: Heat the crushed pineapple. Add juice of lemon and the sugar until sugar dissolves.
Put the gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water and set 10 minutes, then add this to the hot mixture. Cool and put in icebox.
When set enough, add the cheese and whipping cream, beaten stiff.
Stir well and return to icebox.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Separate eggs
and
beat egg yolks.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, spices and
pumpkin.
In double boiler, heat pumpkin mixture, stirring constantly.
Dissolve
gelatin in cold water and add to hot mixture.
Chill until slightly thickened.

title: best mexican beans
directions: Clean beans for any small rocks.
Boil in a large covered pot of water for 1 hour (medium heat).
Add chopped up onion, tomato, garlic clove and well fried bacon, all cut up, to boiling beans and water.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add about a large cooking spoon of bacon grease to beans for extra flavor.
Boil on low-medium heat for about 1 more hour, until beans are soft.
Yum, yum!
Enjoy!

title: coke salad
directions: If using unsweetened cherries, add 3/4 cup sugar. Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill until firm.

title: friendship cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in butter.
Stir in Eagle Brand and pour over remaining ingredients.
Stir and mix well.
Mixture will be very stiff and gooey.
Place on waxed paper and roll into logs. Store in refrigerator almost indefinitely.
Slice and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll in crushed pecans.
Makes 4 cheese balls.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add oil and pudding, mixing well.
Add water and cake mix and beat 4 minutes.
Add poppy seed.
Bake in 2 greased bread pans at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet-n-sassy chicken wings
directions: Combine broth, sugars and soy sauce.
Marinate chicken with mixture in refrigerator for at least 3 hours (overnight is best). Bake wings and mixture in covered dish for 40 to 50 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put in a large pot and boil for 7 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: mexi dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium bowl until blended.
Serve with tortilla chips or Ritz crackers.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Mix rice, water and tomato sauce in a bowl.
Grease 1 1/2-inch deep pan.
Pour in mixture.
Set chicken pieces on top of rice. Sprinkle onion soup on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Remove foil the last 10 minutes to brown.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries; break apart.
Do not mash.
Add pineapple, bananas and half mixture in long baking dish. Chill until firm.
Spread with sour cream.
Spoon rest of Jell-O over top.
Chill.
Cut in squares.

title: chicken or ham pot pie
directions: Cook peas and carrots per package directions; drain.
In a saucepan, saute onions and stir in flour, salt, sage and pepper; add water, milk and granules all at once.
Cook until thick and bubbly, then cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Stir in drained peas and carrots, chicken or ham, parsley and pimento; heat until bubbly.
Turn mixture into a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place pastry over the dish; cut slits in top and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: broccoli 'n' cauliflower salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; set aside. Combine oil and next 5 ingredients, stir well, and pour over vegetables.
Toss gently to coat, cover and chill 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with a slotted spoon over lettuce. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, eggs and molasses. Add all dry ingredients. Mix well. Roll and cut. Bake in 350° oven approximately 12 to 15 minutes.

title: almond chicken dijon
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard until well blended.
Spread top side of each chicken breast half with 1 tablespoon of the
mustard mixture; sprinkle evenly with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.

title: mary's boiled dinner
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown spareribs lightly (cut into 2 to 3 ribs each).
Drain most of oil from ribs.
Leave ribs in pot and add sliced onion.
Saute a few minutes, then add chorice sausage (cut in 2-inch pieces) and kielbasa (cut same).
After browning, add water to cover and cook for 1/2 hour.
Now you may add cut up carrots.
When carrots are half done, add cabbage, cut in 4.
Add potatoes last.
(Cut as you like.)
Cook until done with cover on. If need more water, add it.
Makes a lot leftovers.
Delicious!

title: original chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the white sugar, brown sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Add flour.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.

title: spicy popcorn
directions: Mix all together and enjoy.

title: holly wreaths
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in double boiler. Stir until marshmallows are melted. Pour mixture onto corn flakes and mix. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper and put a few red hots on the top to simulate berries on holly. Serves 24.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in pastry lined pie pan. Top with lattice crust, if desired. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot fudge sauce i
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until mixture comes to a full rolling boil.
Boil briskly 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 1/2 cups. May be stored in refrigerator.
To reheat, place in pan over hot water until sauce is thinned to pouring consistency.
If 3 squares unsweetened chocolate are substituted for cocoa, use 2 tablespoons butter.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter.
Cook for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by tablespoon on wax paper.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 20 pieces.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and add onion.
Put layer of chips in baking dish. Alternate layers of chips and meat mixture.
Mix enchilada sauce, soups and milk.
Pour over meat and add chips.
Top with Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: doughnuts
directions: Use doughnut cutter and make holes in biscuits or make all doughnut holes.
Drop biscuits in hot oil and deep fry until done or light brown.

title: kahlua and eggnog
directions: Combine eggnog and Kahlua in 1 1/2-quart pitcher.
Pour into punch cups.
Top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Line bottom of dish (glass) with slices of angel food cake. Mix vanilla pudding with 1 1/2 cups of milk; beat in 1 cup Cool Whip and spread on cake.
Mix strawberry pudding with 1 cup milk; beat in 2 to 3 containers strawberry yogurt; add some chopped strawberries and layer on filling.
Top with Cool Whip; garnish with sliced or whole strawberries.
Refrigerate; can be made ahead.

title: honey butter
directions: Mix butter and honey and beat with electric mixer until well blended.
Refrigerate in covered dish.
Best to allow to stand at room temperature for 30 minutes before serving.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar. Add eggs.
Mix small amounts of the flour-oatmeal mixture in a blender until it turns to powder before adding it to the bowl. Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Make golf ball size cookies. Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Spread rice evenly in a slightly greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Add chopped vegetables, spreading evenly over rice.
Pour chicken broth and water over rice and vegetables.
Cook sausage until slightly brown; drain.
Spread over vegetables.

title: fast chicken
directions: Use a glass microwave dish.
Spray with cooking spray.
Lay chicken in single layer pushed close together.
Put 4 tablespoons of margarine on and around chicken or use squeeze margarine. Cover with a piece of wax paper and cook for 5 minutes in microwave, then turn and cook another 5 minutes.
Then choose what flavor you want for the night!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.

title: chocolate mint snowman cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together; add all but flour, carrot, chocolate drops and coconut.
Fold in flour.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour in round cake tins.
After they cool, trim 1-inch around the top one and put the full sized one under it.
Take the trimmings and cut a top hat out of it.
Frost it with Chocolate Mint Frosting.
Put coconut on it for snow.
Use end of carrot for nose and chocolate drops for eyes and mouth.

title: patty's pumpernickel bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in molasses, salt, shortening, caraway seed and rye flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough white flour to make dough easy to handle.

title: nutty nut bread
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 13-inch glass loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients, except nuts, beating vigorously hard for 30 seconds.
Stir in nuts. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: creamed potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes into eighths.
Saute chopped onion in butter in heavy 3-quart saucepan for 1 minute.
Add potatoes, garlic and broth.
Simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Puree in food processor or blender.
Add rest of ingredients.
Garnish with crisp croutons, green onion tops or parsley.
May be made ahead and kept refrigerated.

title: italian garden salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain and chill.
Add all ingredients except cheese.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight, if possible.
Sprinkle with cheese, if desired, when served.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Steam cabbage; drain.
Mix corn flakes and margarine and place in the bottom of casserole dish.
Place cabbage in dish.
Mix soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Pour over cabbage.
Place cheese and crumbled corn flakes over cabbage.
Cook in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Stew chicken in a large stew pan with seasonings, in enough water to cover until well done.
Remove chicken.
Mix flour, baking powder, egg, salt, onion and melted butter.
Add enough milk to make a stiff dough.
Thicken chicken broth slightly with flour.
Bring broth to a boil and drop dumplings by the teaspoonful into the boiling liquid.
Turn down heat and cook slowly for 5 to 7 minutes.
Do not cover while cooking.

title: 500 cake(banana)
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake in loaf in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: easy twice baked potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes, beat in rest of ingredients.
Top with 2 Tbsp. melted butter and 1/2 c. shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in buttered 2 qt. casserole dish.

title: curing ham - country style
directions: Weigh hams to be cured.
Cool until body heat is out.
Divide sugar and salt into 3 equal parts.
Use mix at three different times.
First application is when meat is cool.
Second application is on the third day.
Third application is on the tenth day.
Be sure to fill shank end with mixture.
Rub salt on skin, also.

title: dove
directions: Season doves with salt and pepper, roll in flour.
Place in oil in heavy roaster.
Bake at 300° until brown.
Add onions, water and 1 cup sherry.
Bake, covered, until tender, basting with sherry occasionally.
Add parsley to gravy just before serving.

title: cholesterol-free egg substitute
directions: Beat egg whites lightly with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until thoroughly blended.
Yield: 6 tablespoons or equivalent to 1/2 cup commercial egg substitute.

title: j. t.'s brisket
directions: Pierce brisket numerous times with a fork.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and lemon pepper to taste.
Place brisket, fat side up, in a baking pan.
In a bowl, mix barbecue sauce, A.1. steak sauce, lemon juice and Italian dressing to suit your taste.
Pour over brisket.
Seal foil and marinate overnight.
Bake 3 to 6 hours, depending on size, in a 250° oven.

title: magnificent macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir vanilla and food coloring into the sweetened condensed milk until evenly blended.
Fold in coconut until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until delicate brown.
Cool on a flat surface.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: cherry slices
directions: Beat all together at medium speed about 2 minutes until light and fluffy.
Add slowly 2 1/2 cups flour, 1 1/2 teaspoon baking powder and pinch of salt and beat well.
Spread into 11 x 17-inch greased pan saving 1 1/2 cup of batter for top.
Spread 1 can cherry pie filling over dough.
Drop rest of dough over that by spoonfuls.
Spread out.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when done.

title: vanilla cream sauce
directions: Mix the flour into sugar and gradually add boiling water, constantly stirring.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: no cook boiled custard
directions: Stir with a mixer and refrigerate.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Mix well and sit overnight in the refrigerator.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Let sherbet soften slightly, then mix with ginger ale in punch bowl.
Makes 25 servings.

title: crisp pickle slices
directions: Slice thin.
Do not peel.
Add onions, peppers and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt and cover with ice.
Mix good.
Let stand 3 hours, then drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Mix and heat to a boil.
Put in jars and seal. Makes 8 pints.

title: cheese ball(quick and easy)
directions: Let cheese soften.
Mix all together until well blended. Refrigerate until hardened again.
Roll into a ball, then roll into chopped nuts. Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Soften cream
cheese; add confectioners sugar.	Fold in Cool Whip; add
sliced strawberries.
Put in pie shell.	Chill before serving.

title: carrot and coriander pilaf salad
directions: Wash and dry carrots.
Coarsely chop carrots.
Wash and dry 4 large romaine leaves.
Place leaves in plastic bag and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: leftover ham casserole
directions: In a large casserole dish, layer potatoes with some overlapping.
Next, sprinkle on ham, green pepper, onion and cheese.
Mix sour cream and soup together and spread over top.

title: freezer slaw(evelyn parker's)
directions: Sprinkle the salt over the cabbage and let set for 1 hour. Set aside.
Mix the vinegar, sugar, celery seed, water and mustard seed.
Bring to a
boil. Set aside and allow to cool.
Grate the carrot and chop the green pepper. Drain cabbage. Add other ingredients and toss. Refrigerate or freeze in portions to be used later.

title: haystack candies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and pour over oatmeal and coconut mixture.
Mix well, then using a teaspoon, drop mixture (cookie size) onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: pina colada dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in small mixing bowl and beat until well blended.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator. Yields about 1 1/2 cups of dressing.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add beaten eggs, oil and milk. Mix well.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown beef in skillet, drain and return to skillet.
Add salt and pepper as desired.
Slice peeled potatoes and onions and layer over meat.
Mix soup with half can of water in medium bowl.
Pour mixture over meat and vegetables.
Do not stir.
Cover and cook 35 minutes on very low heat.

title: no peek stew
directions: Combine all ingredients. Put in large Dutch oven. Bake at 300° for 4 hours. Do not PEEK.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix and cook until thickened.
Pour into cooked pie shell. Beat egg whites.
Pour over pie. Brown in oven at 400° for about 8 or 9 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Prepare Old Fashioned Fruit Dressing.
Mix fruits and marshmallows; toss with dressing.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Refrigerate leftover salad immediately.

title: flank steak teriyaki
directions: Mix all ingredients, except steak; pour over steak.
Marinate in refrigerator about 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Broil steak in broiler until desired doneness.
Baste occasionally with marinade.
Carve in thin slices, cutting diagonally against the grain from top to bottom of steak.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cran-razz delight
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in the boiling water.
Add the crushed pineapple and the cranberry sauce.
Refrigerate until it is almost set.
Add the pecans and mix them in.
Place in a decorative dish and refrigerate until firm.
In another bowl, mix the sour cream and cream cheese very well.
With a spatula, spoon over the Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, cake mix and 1 egg. Mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle pecans evenly over batter layer.
Set aside.
Combine cream cheese, confectioners sugar and remaining 2 eggs.
Mix well. Spread mixture over pecan layer.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake 45 to 50 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool for 30 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: bald eagle valley tomato salad
directions: Cut tomatoes in chunks to fill a dish.
Dilute the vinegar with water. Sweeten with sugar, mix in onions and pour this over tomatoes.
Sprinkle with black pepper.

title: cracker surprises
directions: Boil together for a minute or so.
Line a jelly roll pan with aluminum foil.
Place Club crackers on foil.
Spread or sprinkle with almonds.
Pour butter and sugar over crackers and almonds. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or less.
Watch very close as they will burn very easily.
Take out and let cool.
Break up in pieces and store in a tin.

title: wine cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixer bowl and beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased angel food pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until candy makes a soft ball when dropped in water.
Remove from heat to cool.
After candy has cooled, beat for approximately 5 minutes. Pour into buttered platter.
Cut into squares when firm.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in chili sauce, horseradish and lemon juice.
Cool until begins to set.
Then add celery and shrimp and place in salad mold.

title: bean and escarole soup with italian sausage
directions: Crumble sausage into microwave-safe 3-quart glass casserole with lid.
Add onion and garlic.
Microwave covered on High power until sausage is cooked through, 6 to 7 minutes.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Break angel food cake in pieces; put in bottom of dish.
Mix strawberry Jell-O with hot water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Pour over cake.
Prepare vanilla pudding as directed on package.
Pour over top.
Add Cool Whip on top.
Put in refrigerator and chill.

title: miso soup for beginners
directions: To
pot
of boiling water, add clams, dashi-no-moto and ebi. After
it
comes
to a boil, lower heat.
Add miso; stir with spoon until miso is dissolved.
Beat egg in a bowl, then stir into soup.
Add tofu and onion.	While preparing soup, do not cover pot or leave it unattended.
After soup is done, you may cover pot and simmer over low heat.

title: orange butter
directions: Bring ingredients to room temperature. Whip orange juice into butter 1 tablespoon at a time and chill. Serve with bagels or muffins.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Mix well and let stand 2 hours.
Squeeze out juice after 2 hours.
Make dressing by boiling sugar, vinegar, water and spices for 5 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Add diced peppers, celery and carrots to cabbage.
Pour liquid over and let stand 24 hours.
Chill and serve.
(Keeps 60 days.)

title: tamales
directions: Soak corn husks in hot water overnight.
Place pork or chicken in large pot with water.
Heat to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Drain; reserve broth.
Shred meat and set aside.
Cover dry chilies with boiling water and soak 30 minutes.
Drain and place in blender with spices and 1 cup broth. Blend to smooth, adding more broth, if needed.
Cook onions and garlic in small amount of shortening.
Add meat and 1 teaspoon salt.
Mix until blended.
Stir into chili mixture and simmer 15 minutes.

title: lorers mincemeat salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Cool.
Add other ingredients. Pour into mold and chill.
Good with ham or turkey.

title: southern dressing
directions: Beat eggs and combine with other ingredients. Pack into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat sugar,
salad
oil,
water and vinegar.
Pour over salad and chill for 24 hours.
Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: lots of flavor hamburger patties
directions: Mix the ground chuck with the crumbled up bread, garlic salt, A.1. sauce and egg together evenly and make into patties.
Add onion to mixture, if desired.

title: crunchy chicken 'n green bean bake
directions: In a
large saucepan, combine soup and milk.
Heat just to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in chicken, rice,
beans, mushrooms, pimiento, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried
onions.
Pour
into
a
greased
2 quart casserole.	Stir.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese
and	onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: mandarin angel cake
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Add orange juice and apricot nectar, stirring until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly 5 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in oranges, reserving 1/4 cup oranges for garnish. Chill thoroughly.

title: foolproof rolls
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Melt shortening in 1 cup warm water.
Mix all together.
Add egg, beaten slightly.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Knead; make into rolls. Let rise and bake in hot (450°) oven.
Uncooked dough can be stored in the refrigerator for several days.

title: bean salad
directions: *Broccoli, carrots, cauliflower, green pepper, onion, etc.

title: sweet potato fantasia
directions: Prepare potatoes according to package directions; cool.
Stir in egg, sugar and salt.
Fold in grapes and pecans.
Pile into 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, in a moderate oven (350°) for 25 minutes.
Top with bacon.
Return to oven; bake 15 minutes longer. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt margarine and seasonings.
Mix together with nuts, cereal, etc. in a large roasting pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, stirring about every 20 minutes.
Let cool on paper towels before storing.

title: strawberry jello pretzel dessert
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, 3
tablespoons
sugar
and margarine. Press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes. Don't let pretzels burn.
Cool.

title: banana salad supreme
directions: Put brown sugar, vinegar, beaten egg and water in saucepan and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
In appropriate dish, place a layer of sliced bananas, then some of the sauce and sprinkle with part of the nuts. Continue with layers until all ingredients are used.

title: polish bow ties(chrusciki)
directions: Mix egg yolks, salt, vanilla, sugar, sour cream and whiskey or rum.
Beat well with electric or hand mixer.
Pour mixture into flour; knead well until dough is soft like noodle dough, or about full 20 minutes.
Roll out very thin; cut strips 2 inches to 4 inches.
Cut 1-inch slit in middle of each strip and pull out one end through.
Fry in deep, hot shortening, turning once until golden brown (about 1 1/2 minutes).
Drain.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes about 3 to 4 dozen.

title: creamy clam dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix Velveeta cheese and cream cheese with electric mixer at medium speed until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with bread sticks, crackers or French bread.
Makes 2 cups.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Spread biscuits flat.
Spoon apples (cubed) into center.
Fold over and pinch shut.
Put into casserole dish.
Mix 7 cups of Seven-Up, sugar, apple pie spice and margarine.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: farmers brownies
directions: Mix cocoa into water. Stir in butter and allow to cool. Sift dry ingredients and stir into cocoa mixture. Add eggs. Beat in buttermilk and then vanilla. Add nuts. Spread on buttered 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: In sauce pan, melt margarine and cheese, add sour cream.
Mix with potatoes.
Spoon potato mixture into greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Top with more cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: homemade chicken pot pie
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
I add a little chicken soup base for flavor. Drain chicken and set aside.
Save the chicken broth.

title: almond bark
directions: Melt chocolate and roasted almonds.
Stir and pour onto cookie sheet.
When cool, break into pieces.
Pan does not need to be oiled.

title: cream cheese danties
directions: Cream together cheese, butter and sugar.
Add almond extract. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to cream mixture, mixing well.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Shape dough in small balls.
Roll in crushed flakes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 1 1/2 inches apart.
Top each with candied cherry.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack. Makes 3 dozen.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add hominy, Cheez Whiz and soup.
Mix well. Sprinkle with corn chips on top.
Bake for 30 minutes in a slow oven.

title: "really quick" salmon casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions (I like to add about 1/2 cup more water than called for to make the rice a little saucier!)
Meanwhile, drain liquid from salmon and clean skin and bones from meat, if desired.
When rice is done, add salmon, leaving meat in good sized chunks, and peas.
Mix lightly. Microwave for about 1 minute to heat through.
Serves 3 to 4 generously.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Wedge potatoes after thoroughly washing.
Mix remaining ingredients and dip potatoes in this mixture. Arrange on a foil lined pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, brushing occasionally with remaining oil mixture.

title: white cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Add shortening, 3/4 cup milk and vanilla; beat 2 minutes.
Add egg whites and remaining milk.
Beat 2 more minutes and bake at 350° until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salt water until tender.
Drain and cut up into small pieces with sharp knife (do not crush).
Mix bacon, pepper, onion, squash and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese over top, then position tomato slices on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer all of each ingredient.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Mash with one tablespoon butter and milk.
Add salt,
pepper and Parmesan cheese.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and green pepper until vegetables are tender; drain.
Add remaining ingredients (except cheese) and heat thoroughly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish. Top with cheese.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: hanky panks
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage with onion.
Drain well.
Add cheese until melted.
Cool slightly and spread onto party rye bread.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli braid
directions: Roll out rolls and cut slits on sides (6-8) with a 3-inch center to put filling.
Mix everything else together and fill. Bake at 350° for 23-28 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat or in a double boiler. Mix flour, sugar and salt and stir into chocolate mixture. Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture is fully thickened, about 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolks well; stir in a little of the chocolate mixture, then pour egg into the hot chocolate mixture and cook about 2 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, cool partially, and stir in vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.

title: potato dish
directions: Cook onion and butter together.
Mix with sour cream, soup and 1/2 of cheese.
Add salt and pepper.
Top with remaining 1/2 of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: maple nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour and granulated sugar in bowl. Cut in 1/2 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press into bottom of greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until very lightly browned.
Beat egg, brown sugar, syrup, melted butter and vanilla in bowl until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly over warm crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until topping is firm around edges and slightly soft in center. Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.
If desired, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil broccoli; drain and place in buttered dish.
Place chicken on top.
Mix soup (undiluted), mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and heat.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese; add croutons.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes until cheese is bubbly.

title: better than duffs bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add both milks, vanilla and spice.
Break buns into small pieces.
Pour milk mixture over buns; let stand a few minutes.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown. Spoon sauce over top as soon as you take it from the oven.

title: cajun barbecued shrimp
directions: Coat nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion and saute until tender; remove from heat.
Add brown sugar and next 6 ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Peel and devein shrimp; place in a shallow dish.
Pour marinade over shrimp, turning to eat both sides.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix together. Make into patties and fry on low heat until lightly browned.

title: 24 hour lettuce salad(serves 10)
directions: Mix salad dressing, mayonnaise and sugar.
Set aside.
Rinse baby green peas with cold water and drain.
Do not cook.

title: mom's lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles. Brown meat in skillet with onion. Stir in tomato sauce, paste, spices and 1/2 cup of water. Simmer 1 hour, adding remaining water as needed. Sauce should be very thick. Mix Parmesan and Ricotta cheeses. Add some parsley to mixture, if desired. Layer in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Add cooked noodles, sauce, cheese mixture and Mozzarella. Repeat layers, then top with a little more Parmesan, if desired. Bake about 30 minutes at 350°. Let set for 20 minutes before cutting.

title: mushroom strudel
directions: In half of butter, saute onions until shiny, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Add chopped mushrooms and salt.
Stir and cook for 5 minutes.
Mushrooms will only be partially cooked.
Butter cookie sheet.
Lay one fillo leaf on the sheet.
Butter it, then spread some mushroom filling and some bread crumbs.
Continue layering buttered fillo leaves, filling and bread crumbs.
Top with fillo. Butter the top layer.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients hard for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir thoroughly and drop by teaspoon. Allow to set and cool.
Usually makes 18 to 20, depending on size wanted.

title: yummy oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together sugars, margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in oatmeal, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and walnuts.
Refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.
Transfer by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Use broth from chicken and may have to add little water to boil the dumplings. When dumplings have softened, then add chicken and cream of chicken soup.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil sliced potatoes.
Fry sliced onion in butter.
Combine with soup and milk.
Put into casserole dish.
Dot with butter. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend together Crisco and sugar together until smooth. In a small bowl, add eggs, food coloring and pinch of salt; add to Crisco and sugar mixture. Separate flour and add small amounts to Crisco mixture. Add buttermilk; blend well. Add in rest of flour. Mix baking powder, vanilla and vinegar together; add to cake mixture. Separate into 4 greased cake pans and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage bread
directions: Thaw bread.
Knead and spread thin (like pizza).
Beat eggs well. Add cheese.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage and drain. Spread egg and cheese onto dough.
Spread sausage over cheese mixture. Roll like a jelly roll.
Oil top with small amount of oil.
Bake for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Fix as on box.

title: 12 cream puffs
directions: Add butter to boiling hot water.
When melted, add flour all at once.
Mix thoroughly and cook over direct heat.
Stir in unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on buttered baking sheet.
Place 2 to 3 inches apart.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool, split and fill with sweet cream filling.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix and cook cornbread according to package directions.
Cool bread and then crumble.
Mix with remaining ingredients and chill.

title: chocolate coconut bars
directions: Boil sugar, shortening, milk, cocoa and salt 3 minutes; add oatmeal and coconut and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar and brown sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Blend in vanilla; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with evaporated milk, mixing well.
Fold in coconut and nuts.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until done.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Brown meat and	onions in skillet until meat is cooked. Add mushroom soup,
milk and tomatoes;	mix well.
Add Doritos and mix together.
Lay
slices of cheese on top. Cover in slow oven or microwave
on
High
until	cheese	melts
and
heated through. Makes 5 large servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and sugar and press into a 10 x 15 inch ungreased pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 375 degrees.
Cool.

title: curry cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese and mix all ingredients into ball.
Roll in coconut or nuts.
Can freeze.

title: taco tasting salad
directions: Mix the last 9 ingredients in blender for dressing.
Let chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Toss salad with dressing just before serving.

title: onion and steak salad
directions: Combine parsley, oil, water, vinegar and garlic; mix well. Combine remaining ingredients except Blue cheese and lettuce. Pour oil mixture over the other ingredients and toss well.
Line a large bowl with lettuce leaves and spoon salad over leaves. Sprinkle with Blue cheese.
Makes 4 servings containing 310 calories each.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Bake yellow cake as directed.
While cake is still warm, poke holes with fork.
Mix small box strawberry Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 1/4 cups strawberry soda pop.
Then pour the 2 liquids slowly over the cake.

title: lime-butter mint salad
directions: Put pineapple in large bowl and sprinkle the dry jello over it and mix.
Add marshmallows and stir.
Cover bowl and place in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, shave or scrape the mints and mix with whipped cream.
Add to pineapple mixture.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until serving time.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: orange cookies by momma jeanne
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs; mix thoroughly. Add juice and milk to creamed mixture. Sift flour with salt, baking powder and soda. Mix well and bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit and sorbet coupe
directions: Gently mix fruit in a large bowl.
Refrigerate to chill. Spoon into individual dessert bowls or goblets.
Slowly pour on ginger ale.
Top with small scoops of sorbet.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth. Add shrimp soup and beat until well blended.
Stir in onion and lemon juice.
Serve with potato chips, pretzels or crackers.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir peanuts, sugar, syrup, and salt in a 1 1/2 quart microwave safe bowl. Cook on high for 4 minutes, stir, cook 4 more minutes. Stir in butter and vanilla. Cook 2 more minutes. Add baking soda and quickly stir until light and foamy. Immediately pour onto greased baking sheet. After cool, break into pieces. Store in airtight container.

title: miniature cream puffs
directions: Put butter and boiling water in a saucepan; place over heat and boil until butter is melted.
Add flour all at once and stir hard.
Cook until mixture is thick and smooth and does not stick to side of pan, stirring constantly so it does not burn.
Place mixture in large bowl of mixer and add eggs one at a time, beating on Number 3 speed for about 1/2 minute after each addition.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased baking sheet 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 35 minutes.
When cool, slice in half and fill with your favorite filling.
Yields 24 small puffs.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix flours, baking powder and salt. Mix milk, honey and oil together, then add to dry ingredients. Stir until moistened, then fold in egg whites. While griddle is still cold, spray with vegetable nonstick cooking spray. When griddle is hot, pour 1/4 cup batter on for each pancake. Cook until brown, turning when pancakes have bubbly surfaces. Serve with Orange Sauce. Serves 4.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Precook chicken.
Layer ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20
minutes.
This recipe can be halved.

title: skeen-hamburger for party
directions: Mix and make into patties.
Can be frozen.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Heat skillet until really hot, add sugar with 1/2 lemon and orange peel, stirring until sugar is caramelized.
Then add the juice of the oranges.
Let the sugar amalgamate with the juices very gradually.
Add the cherries to the sauce and let them cook for a few minutes.
Pour the cherry liqueur over it, then flame with brandy.
Serve with ice cream, whipped cream and decorate with a burning sugar cube previously soaked in rum.
Serves 4.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Mix beef, eggs, bread crumbs, juice, garlic, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Put on foil to 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham on top, then shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Roll mixture as for jelly roll.
Wrap in foil.
Seal edges and ends.
Place seam side down in greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Halve cheese slices and place on top of roll.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.
Serves 8.

title: kash's banana split cake
directions: Combine crumbs and 1/2 melted butter. Pat into bottom of glass sheet cake pan to make a crust.
Combine remaining butter and sugar and mix well.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing thoroughly.
Mix in vanilla.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Drain pineapple, taking some of the juice and mixing it into the pudding and sour cream.
Blend thoroughly.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Serve with cut up fresh fruit, using the pineapple chunks.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil syrup, sugar and water together until it spins a thread 235°.
Add peanuts.
Cook until slightly brown 290°.
Turn off flame.
Add butter, vanilla, salt and soda.
Stir slightly and pour in greased pans.
I use cookie sheet or pizza pans.
Can be stretched some before it cools.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: In small bowl, soak bread crumbs in milk for 5 minutes.
In large bowl, combine meats, egg, onion, salt, pepper, allspice and bread mixture.
Toss gently with fork to combine.
Using hands, gently shape mix into 30 meatballs.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Rinse with cold water. Cut up vegetables and kielbasa.
Mix with pasta.
Add in cheese and Italian dressing and mix together.

title: salmon and eggs
directions: Break eggs into large mixing bowl.
Whip with whisk until well blended.
In large skillet, heat margarine over medium to medium-high heat.
When pan is hot, pour salmon and eggs (mixed well) into skillet.
Cook until eggs are done.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Make a family size recipe of brownies (or your favorite recipe).

title: "mom's" popcorn balls
directions: Remove all unpopped grains from popcorn.
Set aside.
Mix together sugar, butter, syrup, water and salt in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Lower heat and boil until syrup spins a thread.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix well.

title: black forest pie
directions: In heavy saucepan over medium heat, melt chocolate with milk. Remove from heat. Stir in extract.
Pour into large bowl. Cool or chill thoroughly.
Beat until smooth. Fold in whipped cream. Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 4 hours or until set. Garnish with almonds, if desired.
Refrigerate leftover.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook the chicken breasts, celery and onion. Break chicken into chunks.
Place in baking dish.
Mix soups and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing and sprinkle over top of meat. Bake 1 hour.

title: pepper relish
directions: Run peppers and onions through meat chopper.
Cover with boiling water; let stand 5 minutes.
Drain and add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: onion wine soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add chopped onion and mix well.
Add beef broth, celery leaves and potato.
Bring to boiling.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Puree mixture in a blender.
Return to saucepan and blend in wine, vinegar and sugar. Bring to boiling and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in cream, parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco mix together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Layer in order: bean dip, avocado dip and sour cream mixture.
Cover with shredded cheese, chopped green onion, chopped tomatoes and sliced black olives.
Serve with corn chips or Tostitos.

title: lime pickles
directions: Make a brine with the lime and water.
Stir well to dissolve lime.
Slice cucumbers in 1/4-inch slices and soak in lime brine for 24 hours.
Rinse well.
Cover with cold water and drain. Bring vinegar, celery seed, cloves, spices, salt and sugar to a boil and pour over drained cucumbers.
Let set overnight.
Next morning, bring cucumbers and solution to a boil.
Simmer until pickles become clear.
Pack in jars and seal.
Green food coloring may be added to make nice green pickles.

title: peanut butter balls(student favorite)
directions: Mix the ingredients by hand and form into 1-inch balls.
Melt one pound of dipping chocolate.
Cover the balls in chocolate, using a fork to tap the side of the dish to remove excess chocolate.
Put on wax paper covered cookie sheet and place into the freezer for 2 to 3 minutes or until the chocolate is set. This recipe can be halved.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the above, except Ritz crackers and margarine, and place in casserole.
Melt margarine and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Cut meat across grain into 1/4-inch strips, 2-inches long. Brown in oil and push aside.
Stir in soy sauce, broth and sugar. Place mushrooms, onions, celery and shoots in separate sections of skillet.
Do not mix.
Cover, simmer 10 minutes.
Add spinach, simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.
Pass additional soy sauce.
Serves 4.

title: 24 hour potato salad
directions: Heat until cheese melts.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Dot with butter and cool.
Put in refrigerator (covered) for 24 hours.
Take out 1 hour before baking at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: wine cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sherry.
Add cake.
Mix vanilla pudding and spices.
Beat until well mixed.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes.
No need for frosting.

title: berry gelatin salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups hot water, 1 cup cold water and juice from fruit.
Add fruit.
Let set.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Start rice to serve with.

title: tenderloin coating
directions: Let meat set out to room temperature. Mix together ingredients. Put coating on meat. Bake in a 400° oven. When removing meat from oven, let set 20 minutes before cutting.

title: fudge
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix sugar and milk in a large saucepan.
Add oleo. Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes or until 234° on the candy thermometer, stirring constantly, to keep from scorching.
Remove from heat, stir in chips
until melted, then add Marshmallow Creme.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together flour and cinnamon.
Beat eggs and sugar until creamy; add oil and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Add flour mixture and mix; form into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately one hour.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients.
Roll in balls and then dip in sugar. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: quick lunchbox cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of 13 x 9 pan.
Combine all ingredients except chocolate bits and nuts in large mixer bowl. Blend well at lowest speed.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: blender banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, cream of tartar, and salt in bowl.
Set aside.
Put eggs, butter, bananas, and sugar into blender container.
Cover and blend on high until smooth.
Pour mixture over dry sifted ingredients, mix just to combine.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, spread cream cheese. Spread chili over cream cheese.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes or until cheese is bubbly. Serve with Tostitos chips.

title: paco de hayo
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Before serving, add 5 jalapeno peppers, if you like.
It's hot.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Mix gelatin according to directions with sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and freeze..
Remove from freezer and let stand at room temperature for 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot fudge brownies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix in sugar, flour, eggs and cocoa.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar together; add self-rising flour and eggs.
Stir in vanilla and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Do not overbake.

title: potato-puff
directions: Beat well with mixer.
Place in a 1-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix all above (except nuts) and form into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and refrigerate overnight.
Very good and inexpensive to make.

title: almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Combine all in crock-pot or over low heat.
Simmer 30 minutes on stove top.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet and bake according to directions.
Let cool.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing and spread on baked crescent rolls.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, egg, salt and chocolate.
Add dry ingredients sifted together, alternately, with milk.
Drop from tip of spoon and bake in a moderate 325° oven.
Put a teaspoon of chocolate frosting on top of each when cold.

title: toffee bars
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Mix sugar, butter, egg yolk and vanilla. Press in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until very light brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Crust will be soft.
Immediately place candy on crust.
Let stand until candy is soft.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine the Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat on medium speed (electric mixer) until well blended, then beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine the flour, salt and baking soda, then mix into creamed mixture just until blended. Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop spoonfuls of dough 3-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 1 sheet at a time at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy or 11 to 13 minutes for crunchy.
Cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet.
Place sheets of foil on countertop. Remove cookies before cooling completely.
Cookies will appear moist; do not overbake.

title: chili pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 1-quart casserole, layer 2 cups corn chips, onion, 1/2 cup cheese and chili.
Top with remaining 1 cup corn chips.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake an additional 5 to 7 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Garnish with sour cream and olives, if desired.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: hickory nut icing
directions: Mix
together
flour,
milk and salt; cook until thick, stir constantly.
Put
into mixing bowl and beat until smooth the remaining ingredients, then add first mixture.
Beat until creamy.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix canned milk with lemon juice, pecans, drained pineapple and drained cherries.
Fold in the whipped topping and spoon into pie crusts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cherry cheese bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with butter-flavored Crisco.
Set aside.
Chop 1/2 cup of the pecans coarsely for topping.
Set aside.
Chop remaining 1/2 cup of pecans finely.
Combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in Crisco until fine crumbs form.
Add 1/2 cup finely chopped pecans and coconut. Mix well.
Remove 1/2 cup and set aside.
Press remaining crumbs in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until edges are lightly browned.

title: carrot and lentil soup(heart healthy)
directions: Place carrots, sweet potato, onion, garlic, stock and 4 cups water in a large pot and bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender, 15 to 20 minutes. Process mixture in a blender or food processor until smooth. Return to the pot. In a separate medium-size pot, bring lentils and 3 cups water to a boil. Skim off the surface foam with a spoon and discard. Reduce heat. Add turmeric and jalapeno and simmer, covered, until lentils are tender, about 15 minutes. (When pressed between two fingers, they will crumble easily.) Discard jalapenos. Process the lentil mixture in a blender or food processor until smooth and add to the carrot-sweet potato mixture. Season to taste with salt and red pepper. Add basil. Place over low heat to heat the soup through. Don't let it boil vigorously. Heat oil in a small skillet until a light haze forms. Add mustard seeds. As soon as the seeds start to pop, hold the cover over the skillet if the spices start to fly out. Add minced garlic and cook until golden. Pour this oil-spice mixture over the soup. Serve garnished with the croutons and basil. Yield: 8 portions.

title: quick poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add water and liquid shortening.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well.
Pour batter into well-greased Bundt pan.
(Do not flour pan.)
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Let cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Then remove cake from pan and completely cool on a rack.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Blend all but last three ingredients.
Add milk, nuts and poppy seed.
Bake in angel food cake pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. May use 2 loaf pans if you prefer.

title: herb crackers
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients; gently blend with crackers.
Store in refrigerator.

title: orange-buttermilk salad
directions: Combine jello and pineapple with juice in large saucepan. Bring to boil.
Cool slightly and add buttermilk.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill.

title: lime pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and cover with 1 cup lime and 1 gallon water. Let stand 24 hours.
Stir.
Take out and put in clear water 3 hours.
Make brine with remaining ingredients.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a medium bowl, beat cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 2 hours or until set.
Top with pie filling.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Combine bouillon cubes, water, onion, carrots, squash, celery, potatoes and pepper.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add V-8 juice and beans.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Any other vegetable can be added or used as a substitute, or any of the above can be left out.

title: pineapple lime jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add milk, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into Jell-O mold.
Refrigerate until jelled and serve.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cook fish, onion and diced potatoes until potatoes are done. Add salt, pepper, milk and cream corn.
Heat again and serve.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Cook diced sweet potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Cool on a cookie sheet (never cool in water).
Mix olive oil, vinegar, ketchup and mustard in a large bowl.
Add onion, pepper, potatoes and herbs.
Serve warm or cold.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat in milk (small amount at a time), then flour (sifted with baking powder and salt; small amount at a time).
Fold in well beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Bake in large tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken and drained vegetables.
Separate rolls and fill with vegetable/chicken mixture.
Pinch closed and place in pan pinched side down.
Combine chicken broth, cream of chicken soup and pimento.
Pour over rolls.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cook in moderate oven until bubbly.

title: blender cheesecake
directions: In blender, blend eggs.
Add sugar and blend.
Add cream cheese and blend.
Add sour cream and blend.
Add vanilla and blend.
Add Bisquick and blend.
Pour into a spring-form pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave cheesecake in for 1 hour.
Remove and chill.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Simmer soup bone and meat in water to cover well for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove from stock and when cool remove meat from bone; separate into small pieces and put back in stock.
Add vegetables, tomatoes and juice and cook for about 1 hour more.
Freezes well.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and let set overnight.
Serve with rye bread cubes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put in casserole in layers: broccoli, water chestnuts, mushroom soup, onion rings and cheese.
Make two layers.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon patties
directions: Separate salmon with a fork.
Add eggs; stir up very good. Add cornmeal and flour.
Stir.
Add salt and pepper; stir.
Spoon with tablespoon into frying pan at least 1/2 inch deep with lard. Fry until brown.
Serve with gravy and biscuits.

title: idaho potato cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Blend in potatoes and vanilla. Combine flour, cocoa and soda.
Add alternately with milk, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.

title: happy home recipe
directions: Take Love and Laughter.
Mix it thoroughly with Faith.
Blend with Tenderness, Kindness and add Friendship, Hope and Obedience. Sprinkle lavishly with Laughter.
Bake with lots of Sunshine. Serve daily in generous helpings.
Yield:
All the Love and Tenderness you can give to each other.

title: four bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon; remove from skillet, then fry chopped green pepper and onion.
Add these with the chili sauce and brown sugar to beans.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Cut breasts in strips.
Assemble remaining ingredients.
Melt margarine in a large skillet over high heat.
Add chicken and scallions.
Sprinkle with salt and garlic powder.
Cook 6 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add mushroom soup, mushrooms and water. Heat to boiling, stirring until smooth.
Reduce heat, blend in sour cream.
Do not boil.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended. Cover and freeze. Serve when set.

title: homemade baking powder
directions: Sift several times and put in air tight container.

title: crispy baked fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Wash and dry fillets and cut into serving pieces.
Season, dip in oil and coat with corn flake crumbs.
Arrange in a single layer in a lightly oiled shallow baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes without turning or basting.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana cream pie 2
directions: Mix cornstarch, flour, sugar and salt.
Mix enough milk to make a paste.
Scald rest of milk and blend in paste.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add egg yolks and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and cool. Slice bananas on top of baked crust.
Fill crust; cover with meringue and bake at 325° for 15 minutes or use whipped cream.

title: green goddess dressing
directions: In a blender container, combine all ingredients.
Cover; blend until smooth.

title: ole' spoon (or batter) bread
directions: Heat milk to scalding; add melted butter and salt, then slowly stir into cornmeal.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly (do not allow mixture to get too thick).
Add more milk if necessary. Remove from heat and let cool, then stir in well-beaten egg whites and pour into a hot, greased four cup casserole.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot with plenty of butter.
Makes 5 generous servings.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain. Add seasoning, sauce and salsa and simmer for 5 to 7 minutes. In 9 x 13-inch pan, spray Pam. Line bottom of pan with single layer of tortillas (you can cut tortillas to evenly line pan). Put 1/2 of meat mixture on tortillas. In a bowl, combine cottage cheese, egg and oregano. Spread entire mixture over layer of meat. Add another layer of tortillas, then add remaining meat. Top with shredded cheese. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes. Before serving, garnish with diced tomato, sliced jalapenos, green onion and black olives.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Mix
in
order
of ingredients.
Form into small balls. Flatten with fork to make a crisscross imprint.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Colored sugar makes it very pretty.
Bake on ungreased cookie
sheet
at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These cookies are very crisp and tasty.

title: hot herb bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Slice French bread and brush mixture between slices (save 1 tablespoon).
Wrap bread in foil, leaving top open.
Brush remaining mixture on bread and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Heat in oven at 400° for 10 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate date nut cake
directions: Pour nuts, dates, boiling water and soda on dates and let cool. Combine and beat.
Flour pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or more.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
(A delicious, crunchy, cold salad and it doesn't taste at all like sauerkraut!)

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake for 30 minutes or until brown in 350° oven.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy, not stiff.
Stir in pecans.
Mix
sugar, salt and cinnamon together.
Add pecan mixture;
stir well.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes.
Place all four ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Mix well the Crisco, peanut butter, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Drop dough from teaspoons and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bill's hot muffins
directions: Place corn twists in muffin tin (2 breadsticks make 1 muffin) and mold them into the container using your fingers.
Put a spoonful of chilies in the bottom of the muffin cup, then salsa, then top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (according to corn twists recipe).
Serve warm as an appetizer.

title: pesto loaf
directions: In a loaf pan, lay Provolone cheese on bottom and up sides. Spread a layer of cream cheese (approximately 1/2-inch thick). Spread a layer of pesto sauce and sprinkle with chopped sun-dried tomatoes.
Repeat process with Provolone cheese, cream cheese, pesto sauce and tomatoes until full.
Cover top with Provolone cheese and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls, either chill or freeze.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet. Flip over halfway through.
May take longer, depending on oven.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain.
Stir in olive oil, dressing mix and thawed vegetable medley.
(I cook the vegetables slightly.)
Heat and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: best ever pudding
directions: Dip cookies in milk, one at a time.
Layer in bottom of casserole dish.
Prepare vanilla mix by package directions; spread over cookies.
Add a layer of whipped topping and a layer of cookies dipped in milk.
Prepare chocolate pudding by package directions; spread over cookie layer.
Top with remaining whipped topping.
Shave chocolate candy bar over the top.
Chill for several hours.

title: molasses applesauce drop cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream shortening, sugar and molasses. Beat in eggs.
Blend in dry ingredients and applesauce with creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pepper steak
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients in 1 tablespoon olive oil for 15 minutes on low heat.
Add tomatoes.
Make sauce.

title: quick creamy potato soup
directions: In 2-quart glass measuring cup, cook bacon on 100% High power for
four
minutes or until crisp.
Remove and crumble; set aside.
In
the drippings, cook onion, celery and carrots on
100% High
power
for
eight
minutes;
stir and cook ten minutes more
or
until
onion
is
tender.
Stir in milk and bouillon. Cook
again on High power ten minutes or until hot, stirring after
four minutes.
Stir in potato flakes and cook again
on 100% High power eight minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring again after three minutes.
Stir in crumbled bacon.
(For a
richer
soup, add 1 cup leftover cubed cooked chicken, turkey or ham.)

title: cholupas
directions: Put pork roast and pinto beans in large pot and cover with water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook at least 8 hours over low heat.
Serve in individual bowls over corn chips or Doritos or Fritos.
On top, put grated cheese, shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, chopped onion and hot sauce.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Beat both sugars and cream cheese until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and blend well.
Fold in strawberries and then spoon into baked crust.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: party going pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown pork chops in hot bacon fat.
Remove and place chops in a baking dish.
Place a slice of onion and green pepper on each pork chop.
Cover with tomato sauce and bake in a moderate 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: empandas
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Roll out and cut in 2 1/2-inch circles.
Drop a small amount of preserves in circle and seal.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add the boiling water to the oatmeal; let soak for 20 minutes. Cream together the oleo, granulated sugar and brown sugar.
Add the eggs, flour, salt and cinnamon.
Add mixture to oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When done, take out and put the following mixture on top.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Use 2 large cookie sheets.
Break crackers like indicated on cracker and place one next to the other.
Melt butter and oleo in a pan; add sugar and bring to a boil.
Boil for about 2 minutes. Spoon over crackers evenly; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; do not overbake.
Remove with spatula onto cooling rack while still warm.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in 375° oven.
Cool slightly before removing.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: chili
directions: Add all ingredients in 2-quart pan.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer and cover for 10 minutes.
Yields 5 cups.

title: crab wontons
directions: Shred crabmeat.
Blend cheese, soy sauce, garlic, Tabasco and onion; mix well.
Put 1/2 teaspoon in center of wonton skin. Moisten edges with egg.
Pinch corners together.
Fry in oil 2 minutes.
Drain.
Dip in sweet and sour sauce.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour and sugar.
Stir in beer gently and mix until blended (do not overmix).
Pour into well-greased loaf pan (dough will be lumpy).
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Drizzle with margarine. Cool in pan for 5 minutes.

title: apple smiles(eatable)
directions: Take two apple wedges and spread with peanut butter on one side of each.
Place 4 to 5 mini marshmallows on apple wedge side with peanut butter.
Take the other apple wedge and place on top of marshmallows.
There you have an Apple Smile!

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook until brown.

title: oatmeal shot cookies
directions: Mix butter.
Add sugar gradually and mix.
Then add vanilla and mix.
Then add flour, baking soda and oatmeal and mix thoroughly.
Shape into logs and roll in shots.
Then chill for 30 minutes.
Slice cookies and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° until golden brown (45 minutes).

title: pink fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Trim the meat of all fat and cut into strips.
Chop onion, garlic and pimento.
Cut green peppers into strips.
Place diet margarine in a nonstick skillet and heat it over a low heat.
Add the strips of beef and brown on both sides.
Add onion, garlic, green peppers and celery.
Add consomme.
Season the whole mixture with salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Do not boil. Add pimento.
Thicken with cornstarch mixture.
Cover; simmer the addition for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings (1001.4 calories in whole recipe; 250.4 each serving).

title: four layers chocolate dessert
directions: First Layer:
Melt one stick margarine and mix with 1 cup self-rising flour and 1/2 cup nuts.
Press mixture into oblong pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: angel delight
directions: Cook angel food cake according to package directions and cool. Rip into bite-size pieces and place into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix jello according to package directions and cool to semi-solid state.
Mix jello, Cool Whip and strawberries and pour over angel food cake.
Chill for 2 hours and serve.
Serves 10, 40 calories per serving.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased skillet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp spread appetizer
directions: Heat tomato soup and gelatine together until slightly thick. Beat together cream cheese, onion, celery and mayonnaise.
Blend with gelatine and tomato soup.
Add shrimp.
Place in mold and chill about 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, chips and pecans. Form balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; press down with lightly floured bottom of small glass and bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes until edges are golden.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 dozen.

title: poor man's beef stroganoff
directions: Spray frying pan with cooking spray.
Brown ground beef and onions together.
Drain.
Work the flour into the mixture.
Over low heat, add the stock and cook until smooth and thick.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except sour cream.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: apple lasagna
directions: Put lasagna noodles in boiling water until tender, about 3 minutes.
Place 5 of the noodles on bottom of well greased 9 x 15-inch pan.
Put a layer of apple filling over noodles, then layer of cheese.
Repeat with rest of apple filling and top with rest of cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until top is golden brown.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
In a medium size bowl, blend milk, egg and salt.
Add cooked spaghetti; mix well.
Spread onto a greased 14-inch round pizza pan, a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan or a large pie plate.
Combine the sauce, oregano and pepperoni; spread on spaghetti.
Add toppings of green pepper, mushrooms and olives.
Spoon on the Ricotta cheese; top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: crispy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars; add eggs and mix well.
Mix flour, salt and baking soda, then add to the creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Stir in oats, nuts and butterscotch chips.
Mix well (dough will be stiff).
Divide dough in half or thirds for smaller cookies. Roll on greased waxed paper
to make long rolls.
Seal ends and refrigerate 12 hours or longer.
Slice and bake on ungreased sheet (I spray with Pam) in 350° oven for about 10 to 12 minutes until browned.
Let cool on sheet for a minute or so, then remove to cooling rack.
This makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies, depending on size.
Cookies freeze well.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and blend well.
Cover bowl and chill 1 hour or overnight.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Layer in crock-pot in order in 3 layers.
Cook on low 3 hours.
Note:
You may add anything to this that you like on pizza.

title: grilled tuna steaks(catch, borrow, trade or beg for fresh tuna, caught here off spi.)
directions: Slice tuna into 2-inch thick by 4-inch hunks.
Marinate in olive oil and lime.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Grill on hot barbecue grill for about 3 minutes per side.

title: overnight salad
directions: Place lettuce in bottom of bowl, then drained water chestnuts, garden peas and onions.
Spread mayonnaise over top of this. Sprinkle sugar and garlic powder on mayonnaise, then grated cheese.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Put bacon and chopped eggs on top.
Then enjoy.

title: grandma's cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries in water.
Cook just until they pop.
Add sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add jello and salt while still hot. Let cool, then add pineapple, nuts, celery and apple.
Pour into 9 x 11-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
(Keeps well for 1 week.)

title: artichoke pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix egg yolks and condensed milk.
Add lime juice and mix. Blend Cool Whip in.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Beat egg whites with 3 tablespoons sugar until stiff.
Put over pie and bake in 425° oven until lightly brown.
Let cool in refrigerator overnight.

title: easy strawberry salad
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cook until a thick glaze is formed.
If using fresh berries, let cool. If using frozen, add the strawberries and these will help cool the mixture.
Use 2 cups of fresh berries if that is what you are using.
When completely cooled, add a container of Dream Whip; mix well.
Use an 8-ounce carton of Dream Whip; mix well.
Let set in the refrigerator before serving.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together butter and shortening.
Beat in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Blend sifted dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into balls.
Combine 3 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Roll balls in this mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked salmon
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.

title: berlin scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook bacon; drain and keep 2 tablespoons drippings.
Cook onion in drippings and add spinach.
Do potatoes by package instructions.
Stir in bacon, onion and spinach.
Cook at 400° for 30 minutes.
Take out.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: chicken westmoreland
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; cover the bottom with the pieces of dried beef.
Wrap each chicken breast with a bacon strip and secure it with a toothpick; arrange wrapped breasts on the dried beef.
Mix mushroom soup thoroughly with sour cream; spoon over the chicken. (Note: Omit salt and pepper, the dried beef and soup provide plenty.)
The recipe can be made a day ahead to this point and kept covered in the refrigerator.
Bake, uncovered, in a 275° oven for 3 hours.
Yields 4 to 8 servings.

title: chicken dorito delight or mexican chicken
directions: Debone and chop chicken.
Saute onion and garlic in small amount of margarine or oil until tender.
Combine 1 1/2 cups of cheese, soup, Ro-Tel, chicken, broth, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Layer Doritos in bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Pour meat mixture over chips.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Mash potatoes; add onion, pickles, mustard, mayonnaise and boiled eggs.
Mix well.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all of these ingredients together, then add the 3 tablespoons of mayonnaise.
(I use Miracle Whip.)
