Put 1 tablespoon Crisco in a pan and melt in the oven (I use an iron skillet), then pour mixture into the pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: kahlua dip
directions: Mix and fold all together, then cut up fresh fruit (pineapple, strawberries, bananas, apples or any fresh fruit) and dip into this delicious dip.

title: kahlua
directions: Dissolve coffee in boiling water.
Add sugar and vanilla bean. Let cool.
Add vodka.
Pour in gallon jug.
Cap tightly and let stand 30 days.

title: tomato aspic salad
directions: Melt jello in hot water.
Pour in tomatoes and lemon juice. If you want to make this in a ring, double the recipe.
Fill center with cottage cheese.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Cut eggplant into 1/2 to 3/4-inch slices.
Sprinkle both sides lightly with 1 teaspoon salt.
Place on paper towel with a plate on top as weight for 30 minutes.
Rinse slices well and dry on paper towel.

title: fudge bars
directions: Melt butter and chocolate and cool slightly.
Beat eggs and add to chocolate mixture.
Beat in sugar, flour and dry milk. Spread in 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Frost or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mom's white clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil until brown.
Add hot pepper as it it browns.
Add seasoning and saute a
minute or two.
Add clams and clam sauce and cook 30 minutes.
Add white wine and cook 30 minutes more.
Serve over 1 lb. of cooked spaghetti.

title: health cake (gesundheitskuchen)
directions: Mix together butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at the time, then lemon and flour; add milk last.
Mix everything well.
Pour into greased bundt or pound cake pan.
Bake 1 hour on 350°.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients except chocolate chips in bowl; mix thoroughly.
Add chocolate chips and turn into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cool 20 minutes and then turn out of pan.
When nearly cool, cover with foil to keep the moisture in.
Cake is better if you mix it for about ten minutes.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Blend together sour cream and mayonnaise.
Toss first 6 ingredients with sour cream mixture.
Put half of the mixture into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 cup chow mein noodles.
Add remaining mixture and top with 1/2 cup chow mein noodles.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lauren's favorite whopper pie
directions: Crush malted milk balls in a blender or food processor.
Using a mixer, blend ice cream and Cool Whip.
Fold in crushed milk balls.
Pour into pie shells and freeze until serving time.

title: great punch
directions: Mix juice and lemonade together.
Add softened sherbet, then add 7-Up.
Stir, then serve.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl and mix together.
Pour into a buttered 10-inch deep pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french cream of mushroom soup
directions: Fry mushrooms in butter until well cooked and liquid is gone (mushrooms should be brown).
Add garlic and cook until garlic is light brown.
Add flour and cook, stirring until flour is well blended.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Add white wine, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Add water, parsley and dill. Reduce heat; simmer just a few minutes.
Serve hot.

title: squash patties
directions: Stew squash and onions together to make one cup.
Drain well. Mix
with
other ingredients, adding salt and pepper to taste. Shape into cakes and fry golden brown.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in butter. Combine remaining ingredients. Dip chicken into crumb mixture. Place on a greased 13 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Drizzle any remaining butter over chicken. Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: soy-sunflower seed cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients together thoroughly.
The batter will be quite thin. Drop it by the teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheets, allowing space for the batter to spread.
Bake at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes until browned at the edges. Yields 8 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: broccoli and rice magnifique
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine; add remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour into greased 3-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350°
for abut 45 minutes.
This is good with cooked, chopped chicken added for a main dish.

title: modified pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour and beat on medium speed with mixer until well combined.
Stir in flour just until mixed. Pour into 2 lightly greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until tests done.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.

title: breaded baked fish
directions: Combine all ingredients except olive oil in a shallow pan. Pour olive oil in a pie pan and dip each fillet in the oil; roll in the bread crumb mixture.
Place fish in a pan (greased or sprayed).
Bake for about 20 minutes or until fish flakes when tested with a fork.
Bake at 375°.

title: good for the heart brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Spray with Pam and wipe with a paper towel.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Add egg substitute; beat well.
Combine remaining ingredients except powdered sugar and add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Spread in pan.
Bake 10 minutes or until center is slightly firm when touched.
Cut in squares when partly cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Makes 48 brownies, 45 calories and less than 1 gram fat each.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir sugar, milk and butter together, bring to a boil. Continue to boil until a small drop of this mixture forms a ball when dropped into a glass of water. Then add peanut butter and vanilla. Remove from heat and pour into a greased 8x8 inch pan. Refrigerate. Cut into squares.

title: seafood appetizer cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fudge meltaways
directions: Melt 1/2 cup oleo and 1 square unsweetened chocolate in pan. Blend in sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla, egg, cracker crumbs, coconut and nuts into oleo-chocolate mixture.
Mix well and press into ungreased pan (9 x 9-inches).
Refrigerate.

title: soda crackers
directions: Make a stiff paste with buttermilk; beat until light.
Roll tolerably thin; cut into squares.
Prick and bake quickly.

title: fresh summer salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate at least one hour before serving. Serve with chips. You may add more jalapeno peppers if desired.

title: captain crunch bars
directions: Bring your sugar and syrup to a boil.
Set it off the fire and add your peanut butter.
Stir until smooth and creamy.
Pour this over cereal.
Drop by a teaspoon onto wax paper.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: banana pecan torte
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Beat in bananas and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir in pecans.
Bake in three layers at 350 degrees for 30 - 35 minutes.

title: hamburger roll
directions: Saute ground beef and onion until browned.
Drain well.
Mix in barbecue sauce.
On cookie sheet, open crescent rolls to cover bottom of pan.
Put meat mixture in center of pan.
Place cheese slices on top of this.
Fold dough over loaf and seal to look like French bread.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown. Slice to serve.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix hot water and jellos.
Add remaining ingredients and congeal.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Layer corn bread, tomatoes, green pepper, onion, bacon and pickles in a large dish.
Mix mayo, sugar and pickle juice in bowl.
Blend well.
Drizzle over salad.
Toss before serving.
You may need more pickle juice if salad seems dry.

title: golden punch(serves 100)
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Heat to dissolve sugar.
Mix juices and extracts in water and sugar mixture together and freeze until almost time to serve.
Can leave frozen up to 3 months.
Remove 1 hour before.
Thaw and add ginger ale until it makes a slush. Excellent wedding punch.
Serves 100.

title: shrimp, beef and wild rice salad
directions: Prepare on a large dinner plate.
This salad may be prepared individually for as many people as you desire.
Add to recipe according to number to be served.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in airtight container.

title: hot fudge brownie cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Combine margarine, cocoa and water in a 2-quart saucepan; bring to a boil
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured 11 x 16-inch pan. Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: grandma simon's chicken liver pate
directions: Boil chicken livers and all the spices until livers are cooked.
Drain and cool livers, then grind.
Saute onion, celery, parsley and green pepper.
Add this mixture to the liver, adding mayonnaise to obtain desired spreading consistency.
Add pickle relish, olives and minced hard-boiled eggs.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: molasses stack cake
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add molasses with the soda.
Add the ginger, salt and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Pinch off balls of dough and press in a 8 or 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until firm to touch.
Stack and put apple butter or cooked apples between layers.

title: chicken 'n chips
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Mix soup, sour cream and picante sauce until blended.
In 2-quart casserole, layer chicken, soup mix, cheese and chips.
Repeat.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Mix and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes; reduce to 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast of champions
directions: Slightly butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Butter bread on one side, and cut into cubes.
Place in baking dish and set aside. Cook sausage, until it changes color, and drain.
Spread cooked sausage over bread cubes and top with 1 1/2 cups of cheese.

title: frozen mocha cheesecake
directions: In a small bowl, combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
In a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan, pat crumbs firmly on bottom and sides. Chill.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk and syrup.
In a small cup, dissolve the instant coffee in hot water.
Add to chocolate mixture; mix well.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Pour into prepared pan.
Freeze 6 hours or until firm.
If desired, garnish with chocolate shavings.
Return leftovers to freezer.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets; reserve juice in saucepan.
Add all ingredients but beets to reserved juice.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Pour over beets.
Cool.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Makes 3 cups.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat in eggs. Stir in corn syrup and vanilla. Add soda. Mix well. Stir in peanut butter and oats. Stir in chocolate chips and M & M's. Drop dough by spoonfuls to make 2 inch cookies on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Makes 120 cookies.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat butter in pan.
Add onions, peppers and rice.
Cook until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper; simmer 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crumble up angel food cake and mix with 1/2 bowl (large) Cool Whip.
Mix the sugar, vanilla and cream cheese and then add the rest of the Cool Whip.
Mix strawberries and glaze together.
Put on top of cake.

title: easy 7-layer dip
directions: Chop the tomato, black olives and green onions.
Shred the cheese, then layer each ingredient in a serving dish.
Serve with Fritos Scoops corn chips.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all liquids, sugar and salt together.
Then add potatoes, eggs, celery and onion to liquid mixture.
It is good when mixed a couple days ahead.
A little more potatoes can be added if you need to.
Also, it is better to mix the potatoes while they are a little warm. Refrigerate.

title: bread pudding
directions: Melt oleo.
Add eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla to melted oleo and mix together.
Arrange hot dog buns in a Pyrex dish and pour mixture over buns.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes whole.
Peel when done.
Mix the sour cream, parsley flakes, salt, onion, mayo and celery seed.
Slice potatoes and place in casserole dish.
Add a layer of mixture, then another layer of potatoes until dish is full.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Cook
2 sticks margarine and brown sugar together, when boiling,
let
boil for 2 minutes at a hard boil.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour
this hot mixture over 24 to 30 graham crackers (2 inches
square)
which
have
been	laid out on a large cookie sheet.

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.
Take out of the refrigerator 15 minutes before serving to soften the mixture.
Serve with crackers or cocktail bread.

title: old-fashioned baked beans
directions: Place beans and 1 quart water in a saucepan. Bring to a boil. Boil for 2 minutes. Remove from the heat. Cover and let stand for 1 hour. Drain and rinse. Return beans to saucepan. Add salt and remaining water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until the beans are tender. Drain, reserving 2 cups cooking liquid.

title: easy angel dessert
directions: Bake cake according to instructions on box.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: mellow cheese ball
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, green pepper and onion.
Add pimiento and salt.
Stir in pineapple.
Mix in 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Form mixture into a ball.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Chill. Serve with rye crackers.

title: grammy butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg and vanilla.
Gradually add flour until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto
a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten and sprinkle with colorful nonpareils.
Bake until golden with a light brown edge around the cookie.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Cut flour, salt, baking powder and sugar into shortening until mixture is like crumbs.
Add 1 beaten egg and 3/4 cup milk until mixture is moist.
Spread cherries in bottom of a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until top is browned.
Top with vanilla ice cream when serving hot or cold.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain and chop apricots.
Mix ingredients; freeze.
Set out to soften before serving.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan and add vegetables.
Saute about 5 minutes over low heat so butter won't burn.
Sprinkle on flour, mixing well, and add the broth slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook until it comes to a boil.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and mix in thyme and wine.
Let simmer until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.
Puree in blender, return to low heat. Add cream just before serving and heat through.
Do not boil. Serves 4 or 5.

title: hot chicken salad(serves 8)
directions: Combine all except cheese and chips.
Toss lightly.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spread cheese and chips on top. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes (until cheese bubbles).

title: savory fried fish
directions: Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.
Dip into salad dressing, then into crumbs.
Fry over medium heat in small amount of hot oil until crisp and fish flakes.
Serve with lemon.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine ingredients, stirring well.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook, turning, until golden brown.

title: country coqauvin
directions: Dredge chicken in flour mixed with salt and pepper.
Brown chicken in butter.
Place chicken in casserole (with a tight lid) with 3 medium onions, quartered or 12 pearl onions, mushrooms, bay leaf and salt and pepper.
Cover with 1 C wine.
Put lid on casserole.
Bake in slow oven (300 or 325) for 1 1/2 - 2 1/2 hours until very tender.

title: lime punch
directions: Let the first 6 ingredients set overnight.
When ready to serve, put in lime sherbet.

title: minestrone
directions: Saute celery, garlic powder and onion lightly in oil.
Add everything but the macaroni and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add the macaroni and simmer 30 more minutes.
If you don't get a chance to soak the lima beans overnight, put them in a small pot with 3 cups of water (subtract from the 9 cups that you need).
Bring to boil; cover and remove from heat.
Let sit for an hour, then pour beans and water into other soup ingredients before starting to cook.

title: polish kraut
directions: Cut sausage into pieces.
Put all ingredients into skillet. Cook until onion is done.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Combine
oil
and
sugar, beat until smooth.
Add one of the egg
yolks.
Beat
well.
Add hot water.
Add flour, baking powder,
salt,
cinnamon and nutmeg (sifted together).
Stir in potatoes, nuts and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Bake
in 3 greased 8-inch layer pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix
together with fork.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: oat-millet waffles(serves 4)
directions: Blend all ingredients about 1 minute or until smooth texture. Let mixture stand for about 5 to 6 minutes.
Bake on hot waffle iron that has been sprayed with Pam.
Batter will be very thin. Can be made in nonstick skillet.
Bake each waffle 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fried ricotta
directions: Reduce macaroons to fine crumbs and blend until smooth with Ricotta, cinnamon and 4 eggs.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Dip them in beaten eggs and roll in breadcrumbs.
Brown in butter; sprinkle with sugar and brandy and flame to serve.
Delicious and beautiful.

title: "secret" torvend turkey marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: strawberry layer cake
directions: Tear cake into pieces and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix pudding, cream cheese and milk.
Beat until thick. Pour over cake.
Pour strawberries on top of pudding layer. Spread Cool Whip over strawberries.
Refrigerate.
(This also works in a trifle bowl.)

title: chicken chinese style
directions: Saute chicken with minced garlic in pan coated with vegetable cooking spray; cook until chicken is tender (about 30 minutes). Add vegetables and saute until tender.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Pour over chicken and vegetables and cook about 2 minutes or until completely heated.

title: bundt cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Beat first 3 ingredients. Well grease Bundt pan, then dust with sugar and cinnamon mix. Pour in 1/2 of batter, then put in rest of sugar and cinnamon mix. Pour in remaining cake batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes; cool in pan 15 minutes.
Turn upside down and serve.

title: banana cream dessert
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Press onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: quick pecan fudge
directions: Stir sugar, butter, salt and cream over medium heat, stirring constantly; bring to a rolling boil and stir for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, chocolate, vanilla and pecans.
Press in 9 x 12-inch pan; cool and serve.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Beat peanut butter, butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Beat in flour. Stir in 3/4 cup morsels.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle rest of chips over top and spread.
Cool in pan.

title: pumpkin sweets(bilharacos)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in a little oil and fry until browned and cooked.
Roll in granulated sugar and cinnamon.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Combine and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Freezes well.
Goes well with Mama's Potato Soup.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8-inch spring-form pan (I use Crisco).
Mix graham cracker crumbs with melted butter and add cinnamon to taste.
Pat mixture onto bottom and sides of pan and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and add the beaten eggs.
Sift flour, measured and sift with added spices.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk and soda.
Add jam and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Turn into two 9-inch layer cake tins which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes.
Ice with caramel frosting.

title: turkey-day jello
directions: Combine jello with 2 cups boiling water.
(Note:
use juice drained from pineapple, plus enough boiling water to make 2 cups.) Cool. Add, mashing together as necessary to blend, cranberry sauce, orange juice, crushed pineapple, celery and walnuts.
Mix together.
Pour into mold(s) or leave in a large bowl.
Chill until set.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.

title: baked omelet
directions: Whip together and put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Set overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set in the middle.

title: raisin bars
directions: Boil together raisins and water in large saucepan.
Take off heat, let cool slightly.
While still warm, add 1 cup sugar, butter and eggs.
Then add into saucepan flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, soda and salt.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop first 4 ingredients.
Add salt and let stand until Paste is made.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Toss
together all ingredients except cheese and potato chips. Mix
grated
cheese
and
potato chips and put on top. Bake at 400°
about
minutes
or
until cheese melts.
If desired, add 1 or 2 cups cooked rice for volume.

title: oatmeal cake and topping
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients. Let stand 20 minutes until cool. Cream next 3 ingredients. Add vanilla, cinnamon and salt. Add oatmeal last. Bake at 350° in a 13 x 9 x 2 pan 40 to 45 minutes.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine ingredients in medium size bowl and form balls.
Roll balls in confectioners sugar.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Makes 18 to 20 rum balls.

title: greenbean and onion casseroledallas, texas
directions: Mix together, put in a 1 1/2 qt. casserole bowl.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Put some more onions on the top and bake uncovered for 5 minutes or until onions are gold. Salt and pepper for more taste.

title: pineapple frosting
directions: Pour pineapple into saucepan.
Add sugar and flour; cook at low heat until thickened.
Mix in beaten egg whites.
Spread on cake layer.

title: sparkling lemonade
directions: Mix lemon juice and sugar until dissolved.
Add cold club soda. Stir gently and pour over ice.

title: beer meat
directions: This robust version of the classic salad includes a slightly spicier Caesar dressing to complement the grilled steak!

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Top with grated cheese.
Use a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Baker's Joy no-stick spray or grease and flour well.
Set aside.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon; set aside.

title: sloan's tommy tucker cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls and press with fork.
Bake until brown in a 350° oven.

title: south carolina barbecue
directions: Marinate overnight.
Cook in crock-pot until tender (approximately 6 to 7 hours).

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Slice Twinkies in thirds in layers in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Prepare pudding with milk; pour over Twinkies.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding layer.
Crush Heath bar and sprinkle over Cool Whip. Chill and serve.

title: watergate salad
directions: Fold dry pudding mix into Cool Whip.
Add pineapple and marshmallows.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cuban fried rice
directions: Cook rice as directed but use olive oil instead of vegetable oil and omit the salt.
When rice is done, sprinkle soy sauce and toss until rice is brown (lite).
Drain bean sprouts well; add to rice.
Add chopped sliced ham, shrimp, (pork), garlic powder and water chestnuts.
Scramble eggs and fry in butter; add to rice. Top rice with raw scallions.
Mix and serve.

title: uncle harry's noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Bring 6 quarts of salted water to a boil, add noodles and cook "al dente."
(You want noodles undercooked because they will finish in the baking.) Drain.
In a preheated, heavy skillet, saute the ground beef or turkey over medium heat until it is brown.
Drain off any fat.
Add the soups and the garlic powder to the meat and saute for 3 minutes to blend the flavors.
Fold the mixture into the noodles, put in a lasagna pan and bake in the oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
While this recipe serves four, it is easily doubled.

title: strawberry swirl
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly over bottom of a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until set.

title: baked german potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle parsley flakes on top.
Spray pan with Pam.
Bake in square baking pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Spray chicken pieces with nonstick spray; roll in bread crumbs and arrange on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn each piece over and bake another 15 minutes.
Serve with your choice of sauce.
Enjoy!

title: tater tot surprise
directions: In a large skillet, add the hamburger and brown evenly.
When done be sure and drain off any juice or fat.
In a 10 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish spread the hamburger evenly.
Next, mix together the celery soup, milk, instant onion (or 1/4 cup onion), and the pepper.
Pour evenly over the hamburger.
Preheat oven to 375°. Now sprinkle the Tater Tots over the top of dish.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until the Tater Tots are golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: eric's grandmother's waffle batter
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg whites, together in a bowl. Fold in beaten egg whites last.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix and cook together the rice, sugar, vanilla, evaporated milk and milk.
Add raisins and cinnamon.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Put all together in a 2 quart baking dish.
Stir often so it does not scum on the top.
Cook about 1 hour or until brown on the top.
Or serve with nutmeg on top with milk.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except meat and tortilla chips and bring to boil.
Add meat.
Simmer ingredients for 8 to 10 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips with cheese melted on top.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix together and cook at 350° until light brown.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Place cookies in food processor; crush and mix with butter. Press into large, flat, Pyrex baking dish; set aside a handful of cookie crumbs to sprinkle on top of pie.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients together; serve with crackers.

title: blue ribbon sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugars and oil until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix.
Sift 2 cups of flour with soda and cream of tartar.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in remaining 2 cups of flour. Mix well.
Refrigerate 4 hours or more.
When ready to bake, shape dough into walnut size balls; place on a well-greased cookie sheet about 4 inches apart.
Flatten dough using a flat bottomed damp glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pie crust for fried pies
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until coarse-like meal.
Add water 1 tablespoon at a time until dough makes a ball. Roll into 8 small pie crusts.
Add apple or peach pie filling and fry in 1 tablespoon shortening.
Add shortening as needed.
This crust is very flaky and delicious.

title: sensational sauerkraut
directions: Combine all and simmer 3 hours.

title: meat sauce
directions: Saute beef, onions and green pepper, cooking until beef is brown; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix together.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix brown sugar, mustard and catsup together in a small bowl. Put beans, onion and green pepper in casserole dish; add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake 2 hours in a 350° oven, uncovered.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Place broccoli in 9X13 pan and sprinkle with American cheese.
Mix evaporated milk with mushroom soup until smooth and pour over broccoli.
Top with onions.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 15 minutes or until sauce is hot and bubbly.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni until firm, then drain.
Mix well and add mustard for color and enough mayonnaise to coat all ingredients. Spread sliced olives on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Chill and serve.

title: split lemon layer cake
directions: After cake is cool, split each layer to make two.
Fill between each of 4 layers with lemon pudding. Frost top and sides with frosting.

title: shiny top blueberry cobbler
directions: Spread berries in well-greased sheet cake pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice; set aside.
In a medium bowl, stir flour,
1 1/2 cups of sugar, milk, butter, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon of salt until well blended (will be thick).
Spoon over berries; spread to edges of pan.
Set aside.

title: jiffy cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix up ingredients.
Pour in muffin pan and let cook for 20 minutes.

title: baked chicken special
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, paprika, salt and pepper in a large bowl; stir well.
Add chicken, coating well.
Cover and chill 8 to 10 hour or overnight.
Remove chicken from mixture. Coat evenly with bread crumbs.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Combine margarine and shortening; spoon 1/2 cup over chicken. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Spoon remaining margarine mixture over chicken and bake 15 more minutes or until brown.
Makes 12 servings.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix crushed wafers, powdered sugar, pecans and cocoa.
Stir in bourbon and corn syrup.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered or granular sugar.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for several days.
Freezes well.

title: surprise packages
directions: Mix together; spread in hot dog buns.
Wrap in wax paper; place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until soft.

title: creamy double decker fudge
directions: In 2-cup glass mesuring cup with handle, combine peanut butter chips and 2/3 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute or until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Spread evenly into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
In glass measuring cup, combine remaining sweetened condensed milk and chocolate chips.
Repeat same microwave procedure.
Stir in remaining 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; spread evenly on peanut butter layer.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.
Turn onto cutting board and peel off foil and cut into squares.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter meltaway cake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a saucepan and stir over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in flour, sugar, soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix peanut butter and cooking oil.
Spread over cake and refrigerate for 20 minutes.
Heat 1/2 cup oleo and 1/4 cup cocoa until it bubbles. Add 10x sugar, buttermilk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread over peanut butter mixture and cool.

title: easy layer bars
directions: Pour melted butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over melted butter.
Sprinkle coconut evenly over crumbs.
Top with chocolate chips, then nuts.
Pour milk over entire mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned on top.
Cool.

title: caramel fluff topping
directions: Put chilled whipping cream in glass bowl.
Whip a little; add brown sugar.
Whip a little more.
Add vanilla and whip until it's fluffy.

title: mylett's steak marinade
directions: Mix all together, pour over steak and let sit, then barbecue and enjoy.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Dip balls in this and place on wax paper to set.

title: shower punch
directions: Mix orange juice, lemonade, water and sugar in container and refrigerate overnight.
Right before serving, add the pineapple juice.
Divide ingredients in half and use half of juice mixture with 1 bottle of ginger ale over ice.
Serves 50 to 75 people.

title: fried rice
directions: Cut meat into bite-size pieces.
Heat oil in skillet or wok. Cook meat on high, stirring constantly for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in carrots; cook for 3 minutes.
Add onions, water chestnuts, mushrooms, pineapple and soy sauce.
Stir 2 to 4 minutes.
Add already boiled rice and cook on low heat for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: angel dessert
directions: Mix gelatine, water and juices and bring to a boil. Add sugar and cool in refrigerator.
Break cake into pieces.
Whip the cream and fold into jello mixture.
Add cake pieces and carefully blend. Spread into casserole dish and sprinkle top with coconut. Chill.

title: creole okra
directions: Saute onion and cook green pepper in bacon drippings until tender.
Add okra; cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Add water if needed.

title: can tomatoes
directions: Scald
and
peel tomatoes.
Fill in jars.
Use a little salt if
desired.
Put into oven on a pan and bake at 250° for 45 minutes if using pint jars.
Quart jars take longer.

title: marki's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 450° until brown.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Layer the vegetables in order listed.
Seal top with mayonnaise.
Mix cheese and sugar; sprinkle on top.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, sprinkle bacon or Bac*Os on top.

title: soap
directions: This is my grandmother's recipe and I was scrubbed clean many a time.
No way does it compete with Dove or Ivory and I submit this to remind us life was not so easy in the "good old days."

title: lemon shrimp salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; allow to cool and partially set.
Add and fold in the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: oatmeal pecan cookie
directions: Blended oatmeal measure and blend in a blender to a fine powder.
Cream butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Add chocolate chips, Hershey Bar and nuts.
Roll into balls and place 2 in. apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 375 degrees for 6 minutes.
Makes 112 cookies, recipe can be halved.
Roll to size of walnuts do not press.

title: slow cooker padre punch
directions: Put in crock-pot.
Cook slow for 4 to 6 hours.

title: yeast cakes
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in order; let stand overnight.
In morning, add soda in warm water.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: deep dark chocolate pie
directions: Mix together milk and chocolate over a low temperature to scald.
Mix flour, sugar and salt in a separate pan. Pour milk and chocolate mixture gradually into flour mixture.
Put this mixture over low temperature and stir constantly! When mixture begins to thicken, stir in egg yolks slowly.
Cool, then add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake at 375°.

title: chicken gumbo soup
directions: Combine water and chicken bouillon cubes in soup kettle.
Add carrots, onions, green pepper, celery, tomatoes, okra and rice. Heat to boiling, turn down heat and simmer for 1 minute (until vegetables are tender).
Add soy sauce and diced chicken.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: minced eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant; cut in slices.
Cook in boiling, salted water for 10 or 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash.
Saute onion in butter until soft.
Combine eggplant, onion, crumbs, soup, 3/4 cup cheese, pimentos and seasonings.
Add well beaten eggs.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with other 1/4 cup of grated cheese.
Bake in moderately hot oven for about 30 minutes at 375°.

title: oriental salad
directions: Combine broccoli cole slaw, Ramen noodles, toasted almonds, sunflower seeds and green onions.

title: sweet potatoes with pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a greased baking dish.
Put marshmallows on top, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cocktail sausages in sauce
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix all ingredients.
Stir in cocktail sausages.
Microwave at 7 for 8 to 10 minutes or until hot, stirring two times.

title: chili fried shrimp
directions: Marinate shrimp with egg white, 1 1/2 teaspoons cornstarch and wine.
Prepare and hold lemon juice, chicken broth, sugar and salt.
Mix and hold 2 teaspoons of cornstarch and water.
Heat wok on high for 30 seconds; add oil.
When hot, add peppers and onion.
Stir-fry until peppers are blackened and aroma escapes. Add shrimp; stir-fry 1 minute until pink.
Stir lemon-sugar mixture.
Add; stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes more until sugar is dissolved.
Stir cornstarch mix; add slowly, stirring rapidly until thick and glossy.
Serve in prepared chafing dish.

title: easy fruitcake
directions: You can use 3 cups of mixed fruit instead of candied cherries and pineapple.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugars in large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture.
Stir in 1/2 cup candies.
Drop by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Decorate with remaining candy.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir peanut butter bar mix, margarine, water and egg together thoroughly in a medium bowl.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until light golden brown.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Squeeze packet of frosting about 10 seconds and frost each cookie with packet of frosting.
Makes 2 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: peanut butter delight(unbaked oatmeal cookies)
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk together.
Heat until boiling, then cook 2 minutes.
Take off heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: cooked carrots
directions: Cook carrots; drain.
Add tomato juice, pepper, onion, oil, sugar and mustard.
Stir together.
Ready to serve.

title: cole slaw for 10
directions: Shred cabbage and add ingredients.
One head of cabbage will yield about 10 to 15 servings.

title: saw meal corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, sour cream, corn and oil together.
Add pepper and onion to taste.
Pour into greased baking pan.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown beef and drain; add Pizza Quick.
Press biscuits into a greased muffin pan.
Fill with beef mix; top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, milk and oil in mixer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Punch holes in cake as soon as it comes out of the oven.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and pina colada and pour over cake.
Frost top with Cool Whip and coconut. Keep refrigerated if it is humid.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Melt butter and add other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Mold into fingers and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat, let cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together salt, flour, baking powder and soda. Add to sugar/egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Form in three rolls (about 1 1/2-inches in diameter) and refrigerate overnight.
Slice thin and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Do not let them get too brown.

title: french dip sandwiches
directions: Remove and discard all visible fat from the roast.
Place trimmed roast in a slow cooker.
In a medium bowl, combine soy sauce, bouillon, bay leaf, peppercorns, rosemary, thyme, and garlic powder.
Mix all together and pour the mixture over the roast.
Add water to almost cover the roast.
Cover slow cooker and cook on low for 10-12 hours until meat is very tender.
Remove meat from broth.
Reserve broth.
Shred meat with a fork and distribute on rolls with sliced cheese for sandwiches.
Use reserved broth for dipping.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix dry cake mix, yeast and flour thoroughly.
Add hot water and mix well.
Let rise to double in size.
Cut in half; roll to rectangular shape.
Melt butter and spread over rolled dough. Sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Roll like a jelly roll; cut in 1 1/4-inch slices.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Repeat with remaining dough.
Cover and let rise to double in size.
Mix together 1 stick melted butter, brown sugar and corn syrup.
Spread over top of roll just prior to baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Be sure cookie sheet has sides.

title: roasted honey pepper pack
directions: Carefully score roast 1/2-inch deep completely around roast without cutting string. Combine all remaining ingredients.

Mix well. Spoon or brush 2/3 of the honey mixture over pack to coat. Roast at 325° for 1 hour. Brush with remaining honey mixture and cook 30 minutes more or until thermometer registers 160°. Serves 8.

title: cheese-stuffed french toast
directions: *Sliced strawberries or bananas, blueberries, raspberries or orange segments may be used.

title: orange-pineapple cool whip dessert
directions: Put dry jello in bowl.
Add drained pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Mix until jello is dissolved.
Add cottage cheese and mix.
Stir in Cool Whip and mix well.
May top with crushed nuts if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients (except the chow mein noodles) in a large bowl.
Place 1/2 the noodles in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Top with the rest of the noodles.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello to dissolve, then add fruit juice. After this has slightly jelled, add blueberries and pineapple (about 45 minutes in an oblong glass dish).

title: chocolate-caramel-pecan cheesecake
directions: Unwrap caramels; combine caramels and milk in a heavy saucepan; cook over low heat until melted, stirring often.
Pour over graham cracker crust; sprinkle toasted pecans evenly over caramel layer and set aside.
Beat cream cheese at high speed with an electric mixer until light and fluffy; gradually add sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate; beat until blended. Spoon over pecan layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and run knife around edge of pan to release sides.
Let cool to room temperature on a wire rack.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
When ready to serve, remove cheesecake from pan; arrange pecan halves around top edge of cheesecake.
Yields one 9-inch cheese cake.

title: easy ham and cheese bake(preparation time:  20 minutes)
directions: Saute green onion or leek in butter in a skillet until soft, but not browned.
Cut ham in thin strips.
Layer ham and onion or leek in a greased casserole or in small custard cups or individual ovenproof serving dishes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with tomato slices and sprinkle with pepper and salad herbs.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, if used.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for about 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and dishes are heated through. Serve immediately.

title: apple pie(nanny helen's)
directions: Pare, core and slice apples.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, salt and cornstarch.
Arrange apples in closely packed layers in pastry lined pie plate, sprinkling sugar mixture over each layer. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon lemon juice over apples.
Dot with butter. Place top crust over filling.
Seal with flute.
Brush top with cream.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 375° for 40 or 50 minutes.

title: carrot ring
directions: Cook carrots in water until tender. Drain and mash. Add Triple Sec, melted butter, basil and pepper. Place in buttered ring mold. Refrigerate until ready to bake.
Cook at 375° for 20 minutes. When done fill center with cooked green peas, lima beans or other green vegetable.
Unmold.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar. Mix the eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg. Add the coconut and crushed wafers and fold in the pecans and milk. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: mexican chili bean slaw
directions: *You can substitute broccoli slaw for cabbage and carrots.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add chili beans already drained.
Stir meat and beans.
Add lettuce, tomatoes, onions, cheese, Doritos and salad dressing.
Mix well.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain.
Pour into large ovenproof bowl and mix in green beans and uncondensed tomato soup.
Top either in dollops or spread like a crust the mashed potatoes. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Take out and top with cheese and bake an extra 5 minutes.
Remove, let cool for 10 minutes and serve.

title: porky-pine balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup.
Form into golf ball size balls.
Arrange in a covered baking dish.
Top with a mixture of tomato soup and 1/4 cup water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar-spiced pecans
directions: Toast pecans 10 minutes at 300°.
Combine all ingredients except nuts and vanilla.
Cook until syrup spins a small thread, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add nuts and vanilla.
Stir quickly until syrup crystallizes.
Pour onto buttered platter. Rapidly, but gently, separate nuts.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Simmer for about 30 minutes or longer until desired consistency is reached.
Can in pint jars.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Layer cucumbers and onions.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cucumber layer.
Store in jars in refrigerator for 1 week before eating.
Makes 4 1/2 to 5 quarts.

title: better than sin cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directions on box and cool.
Cook together pineapple and brown sugar until juice thickens a little.
Cool; spread this over cake, then a layer of coconut.
Mix pudding and milk together; spread over cake.
Next, layer Cool Whip and top with coconut.

title: rick's favorite casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic.
Add ground beef and brown.
Drain liquid.
Add black pepper.
Cook through.
Add two cans of cream of mushroom soup.
Cover and simmer while cooking noodles.
Make noodles according to directions.
Cook vegetables half done and add to hamburger mixture.
Simmer.
When noodles are finished, drain and add to meat mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: coleslaw souffle salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Blend in mayonnaise, cold water, vinegar and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Beat until fluffy. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into individual molds or a 1-quart mold.
Chill until set.

title: cheese balls
directions: Blend ingredents well.
Put saran wrap in a large enough bowl to hold mixture.
Place in refrigerator a few hours or overnight. Use saran wrap to form a ball after it is thoroughly cooled.
Then roll in 1 cup of broken pecans.
Serve with Townhouse crackers or similar cracker.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix altogether.
Preheat oven to 350° or 400°.
Bake until brown.

title: chocolate ice cream roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line jelly roll pan with aluminum foil; spray with Pam.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add
1/2 package of dressing. Mix.
Add other ingredients
and
top
with
remaining dressing mix.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles in boiling water until tender, about 15 minutes; drain.
Break Italian sausage into small pieces; cook in pan.
Put on paper towel to drain excess fat.
Mix together Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, pepper, eggs and parsley.
Divide spaghetti sauce into 4 equal parts.
Divide noodles into 3 equal parts.
Divide Ricotta cheese mixture into 2 equal parts.
Divide sausage into 2 equal parts.
Divide Mozzarella cheese into 3 equal parts.

In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, assemble lasagne layers as follows: spaghetti sauce, noodles, Ricotta cheese mixture, sausage, spaghetti sauce, Mozzarella cheese, noodles, Ricotta cheese mixture, sausage, spaghetti sauce, Mozzarella cheese, noodles, spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until mixture is bubbling.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes to set layers.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: meat in a slow cooker
directions: Crush either BBQ Chips or plain chips.
Melt 1 or 2 sticks butter.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Stir ingredients together in order as listed.
After adding the last ingredient, beat with a mixer to get the lumps out.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix well and pour into a greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mother's country-style steak
directions: Cover and bake in oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Keep covered and you will have a delicious brown gravy.

title: pineapple tarts
directions: Cream sugar
and Crisco.
Add cracker crumbs, milk, egg yolks, baking powder, vanilla
and
nuts.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Hollow out large loaf of bread.
Fill with dip.
Use pieces of bread for dipping.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons of the butter with the oil in a large saucepan.
Add onion and saute for 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour and stir well with a wooden or Teflon spoon.
Add broth, sugar and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into blender and blend at high speed for 30 seconds.
Strain into saucepan and add cream.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring in remaining butter.

title: elizabeth's yeast rolls
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add yeast to this mixture, then add flour to first mixture.
Store in airtight container. Grease muffin tins well or use paper cups; fill about 3/4 full. Cook until done.
This will be very thin.
Cook as you use or need; will keep in refrigerator about one week.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked (well drained) chopped broccoli in flat baking dish.
Cover broccoli with cubed cooked chicken breast.
Combine lemon juice, mayonnaise, curry powder and onion salt.
Pour over broccoli and chicken layer.
Top with cheese and then buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: herbed string beans
directions: Cook beans until tender, but still crunchy.
Melt butter; add garlic and saute.
Add spices; pour over beans.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: brunswick stew
directions: In a 5-quart heavy pot, stew chicken, water, bacon, onion and salt for 2 hours over medium low heat.
Remove chicken; cool, skin and remove meat from bones.
Cut into medium size pieces.
Return to pot.
Add remaining ingredients, except corn; cook 1/2 hour. Add corn and cook 1/2 hour.
Mix butter and flour; add to stew and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: creamy potato casserole
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until done.
Mash
potatoes with sour cream, cream cheese and margarine until
creamy.
Add
a small amount of milk if potatoes are
stiff.
Sprinkle
dried chives onto mixture and fold in.
Place
mixture
in
greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not brown. Can be made ahead of time and refrigerated.

title: double quick yeast rolls
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Measure flour. Stir sugar, half of flour and salt into yeast.
Beat with spoon until smooth; add egg and shortening.
Beat in rest of flour until smooth.
Scrape sides of bowl and cover with cloth.
Let rise in warm place (85°) until double, about 30 minutes.
Grease 12 large muffin cups.
Stir down raised dough.
Spoon into muffin cups 1/2 full.
Again let rise in a warm place until dough reaches top of muffin cups, 20 to 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: carrot curls and celery fans
directions: Peel the carrots.
Use a vegetable peeler to make long, wide carrot slices.
Curl each carrot strip around your finger.
Stick a toothpick through the curl to hold it together.
Soak the carrot curls in ice water for 1 hour.
Remove toothpicks before serving.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat oil in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan over low heat.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes or until thickened.
Pour over ribs (browned) or chicken in a baking pan and bake, covered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Yields about 3 cups (enough to cover 6 servings chicken or ribs).

title: mexican lasagna(yield: 8 servings)
directions: 1. Cook lasagna noodles according to directions.
Drain. Separate lasagna and lay out flat on wax paper to keep from sticking.

title: "jennifer" soup
directions: Put all ingredients together in large pot and cook on low for about 45 minutes to an hour.
Served with hot cornbread.

title: crawfish dip
directions: Melt butter and saute green onions and crawfish tails.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons flour until it makes a stiff paste.
Add mushrooms and parsley.
Add salt, black pepper and cayenne to your taste. When ready to serve, add exactly 12 ounces sour cream and heat. Serve from chafing dish with assorted crackers, Melba rounds or small party shells.

title: grandma's hungarian coffee cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, cinnamon and 1 stick of butter. Take out 1 cup of the mixture and set aside.
Add milk, water, baking soda and salt to the main mixture.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle mixture you set aside over top of the batter.
Melt the second stick of butter and pour over top of the coffee cake.
Bake at 350 for 30-35 minutes.

title: smoked sausage-n-noodles
directions: Slice sausage in 1/2-inch chunks.
Cut onion and peppers in strips.
Add 1 tablespoon of margarine.
Turn heat on medium-low. Cover.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add mushrooms.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Mix with sausage, onion and peppers.

title: cool delight
directions: Step 1:
Mix and press flour, margarine and nuts in bottom of an oblong dish.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: poor man's gravy
directions: Make a paste with lard and flour in meat drippings and thin with milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Beat until smooth the cake mix, vanilla pudding, oil, sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together sugar, nuts, cocoa and cinnamon.
Alternate batter with dry ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 hour in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Fry everything except cheese and eggs until brown.
Then mix in your eggs and cheese.
Pour into pie shell and bake about 30 minutes, until golden brown at 350° (preheat).

title: peach cobbler
directions: Spread peaches in bottom of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients. Spread over peaches.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: cauliflower-bacon salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces. Place in large bowl. Slice onion on top of lettuce. Fry bacon until crisp; crumble on top of onion. Cut cauliflower into small pieces; place on top of bacon. In small bowl, mix sugar, cheese and mayonnaise. Spread over cauliflower; seal against edges of bowl. Cover with Saran Wrap. Best when made the day before serving. Mix thoroughly before serving.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Mix together and bake at 275° for five hours.
Don't touch during baking.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Combine sauerkraut and salad dressing; spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with corned beef and cheese. Place bread, buttered side up, over the top. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through and bubbly. Serves 4.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together and pat into pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Mix balance of ingredients and our over baked crust. Return to oven for 15 more minutes.
Serve warm with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: orange gelatin mold
directions: Drain oranges; measure syrup from oranges.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add measured liquid.
Add sherbet by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in oranges.
Chill until set.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix Crisco, salt and flour with fork or pastry cutter into small nuggets.
Add water and mix with fork until you can form balls.
Roll out desired size.

title: yellow fruit punch
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Remove from freezer and let thaw at least 3 hours.
Add 1 quart ginger ale.
Serves 50 people.

title: zabaglione
directions: In the top of a double boiler, beat together the yolks, the wine and 3 tablespoons of the sugar.
Place the double boiler over simmering water.
Whip mixture constantly with a wire whisk until it is thick enough to retain a slight peak when the whisk is withdrawn (about 5 minutes cooking time).
Taste for sweetness.
If it is not sweet enough, add the remaining sugar.
Pour into stemmed glasses and serve at once.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat.
Drain and crumble.
Add balance of ingredients and simmer for several hours.
Serves 100.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Cook sausage until brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain well; reserve drippings.
Add margarine to drippings to measure 1/4 cup. Set sausage and drippings aside.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add wings and bake at 350° about 1 hour, then put under broiler to brown.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°, bake for 40 minutes.
Mix flour, sugar and soda together.
Add egg, oleo and pineapple; mix.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let set in refrigerator one hour for the flavors to blend.

title: peach cheese delight
directions: Drain and save juice from canned fruit.
Add water to make 2 cups.
Dissolve jello with boiling water.
Add 1 cup fruit juice. Add fruit to jello.
Chill until firm.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Soak raisins, dates and soda in boiling water; cool to lukewarm.
Thoroughly mix the remaining ingredients, using enough flour to make a heavy batter.
Add to date mixture.
Bake in large loaf pan or 2 small pans for 1 hour.
Cool before slicing.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Soak yeast in lukewarm water 5 minutes without stirring; stir well before adding to milk mixture.
Add eggs and shortening; stir well.
Gradually add flour; knead well.
Place in greased bowl; let rise.
Punch down; let rise again.
Punch down; shape into rolls. Let rise and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: peach pretzel salad(serving size: 18)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press into large greased Pyrex dish. Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine graham crackers, margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and 3/4 cup nuts.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat egg whites until very stiff and set aside.
Cream the 1 cup sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Fold egg whites into creamed mixture. Do not beat.
Pour on top of crust and bake at 350° for 23 minutes.
Cool on counter, then refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours until cold. Spread pie filling on top.
Ice with Cool Whip. Sprinkle remaining nuts on top. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 12.

title: basic cream pie
directions: Scald milk; mix dry ingredients together.
Add hot milk, slowly, stirring well.
Add butter; cook in double boiler until thick and smooth, about 15 minutes.
Stir often.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add a little hot filling.
Stir quickly into mixture. Stir and cook 2 minutes.
Cool and add flavoring.
Pour into baked and cooled pastry shell.
Cover with meringue (made with 3 egg whites).
Brown in a slow oven.

title: flashy baked beans
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir bacon and onion until bacon is crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat until bubbly. Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally (15 to 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed).

title: south of the border salad
directions: In skillet cook sausage or ground beef, onion and garlic until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, undrained tomatoes, chili peppers, flour, and chili powder. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.

title: b.l.t. soup
directions: Brown bacon; remove from pan and set aside.
Reserve 1/2 cup drippings.
In remaining drippings, saute onion and celery until tender.
Mix in 1/2 cup flour.
Add vegetable juice, tomatoes, stock, sugar, oregano and reserved bacon.
Add additional flour that has been mixed with a little water, if mixture is not thick enough.
Texture should be similar to that of a thick white sauce. Simmer about 30 minutes.
Add lettuce to soup in pot and serve immediately or top individual servings with lettuce.
Makes about 2 gallons or 15 to 20 large servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Stir until melted.
Add rice, soup, broccoli.
Stir until blended.
Pour in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple-sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender.
Peel potatoes and mash. Add next 8 ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut, if desired.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Remove 1 cup of apple juice; add grape juice and vinegar.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Drink 3 ounces daily.

title: cornbread 2
directions: Mix all together and bake in 400 degree oven for 20 to 25 minutes in well greased pan.

title: chocolate amaretto balls
directions: In a heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate morsels with milk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Amaretto and extract. Chill 2 hours.

title: sweet story cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl. Drop in Spry* (Crisco). Combine milk and maraschino juice. Add 3/4 cup of this liquid. Add flavoring extracts. Beat 200 strokes (2 minutes by hand or on mixer at low speed). Scrape bowl and spoon or beater. Add remaining liquid and egg whites and beat 200 strokes (2 minutes on mixer at low speed). Add cherries and nuts; blend. Bake in 2 deep 9-inch Spry* coated layer pans in moderate oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool. Cut layers into heart shapes, using paper pattern. Spread with Pink Valentine's Day Frosting.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in water in large kettle until tender. Meanwhile, in mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, butter and soup; stir well.
Add milk and salt and pepper.
Add to vegetables and heat through.

title: hamburger finger links
directions: Make in small loaf (size of finger).
Roll in corn flake crumbs.
Brown in skillet of oil.
Place in baking dish.
Pour 1 jar of Heinz homestyle gravy over finger links.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, depending on your oven.

title: fruit dumplings
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over dumplings.

title: sparkling christmas punch
directions: Combine juices and sugar in pitcher.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill in refrigerator.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 16 cups.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Bake in iron skillet at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. You can substitute 2 cups of fresh broccoli for frozen or 1 box of chopped frozen spinach.

title: spinach and potato pie
directions: Wash spinach; chop fine and set aside.
Shred potatoes and onions into eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Spread half of potato mixture in shallow baking dish; spread spinach for second layer and top with remaining potatoes.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes, or until potatoes are browned and done.

title: chili
directions: Combine beef, garlic and onion in large skillet and cook slowly about 10 minutes. Drain and add remaining ingredients in large crock-pot or regular pot. Mix together and add meat; cook slowly about 6 to 7 hours.

title: date nut cookies
directions: Sprinkle soda over dates; add boiling water.
Stir well.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in dates, coconut or nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour; mix well.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until browned.

title: how to preserve children
directions: Mix children well together.
Put in the field, stirring constantly with lots of love.
Pour the brook over the pebbles. Sprinkle the field with flowers.
Spread with a big blue sky. Bake in hot sun.
When thoroughly tired, remove and set to cool in bath tub.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat Eagle Brand milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add Bisquick and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: moist and minty brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In small saucepan, combine sugar, butter and water.
Bring just to a boil; remove from heat.
Add 1 cup of mint flavored morsels and vanilla, stirring until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Transfer this to a larger mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in flour mixture and remaining mint chocolate morsels.
Spread into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes just until center is set.
Cool completely before cutting into squares.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: chicken enchiladas(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Stir chicken, bell pepper, cream cheese and 1/2 cup salsa in saucepan on low heat until cream cheese is melted.

title: doris' zucchini bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add 3 eggs (beaten until foamy), oil, vanilla and zucchini.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 65 minutes.

title: black magic
directions: Mix crushed cookies with melted margarine.
Spread on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Soften ice cream and spread on top of frozen cookies.
Refreeze.
Mix together evaporated milk, margarine, sugar and chocolate.
Boil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Put on top of ice cream. Return to freeze.
May be served with whipped cream.

title: key lime pie
directions: If using frozen packaged pie shell or 6 ounce packaged cracker crumb pie crust, use 1 can condensed milk, 3 egg yolks and 1/2 cup ReaLemon.
Bake 8 minutes.

title: poached pears with chocolate sauce
directions: Select 5 to 6 large firm pears, peel and core leaving stems attached.
Slice about 1/4-inch off bottom so pears stand up. Place pears in enough water to cover them and add 2 tablespoons lemon juice to water to prevent the fruit from browning.
Place water, sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon in a 4-quart saucepan. Over medium heat, stir until sugar is dissolved and syrup is slightly thickened.
Boil 5 minutes.
Place pears in syrup. Reduce heat to simmer and poach for 15 to 20 minutes or until pears are tender, but firm.
Remove pan from heat and cool for 20 minutes or better yet, leave pears in liquid and refrigerate overnight.

title: cocktail wieners 2
directions: Cut wieners into 4 pieces.
Mix all ingredients together and heat.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, salt and milk. Mix well.
Place in heavy saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring until warm.
Combine sugar and flour.
Gradually add to milk mixture, stirring constantly, until thick.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and peanut butter. Let cool slightly.
Pour filling into cooled pie shell. Chill thoroughly. Garnish with whipped cream and peanuts.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, baking powder and vanilla and mix well.
Add milk and flour, mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Let cool, then roll in crushed crackers.

title: cole slaw
directions: In saucepan on stove, combine ingredients. Bring to boil. Pour over cabbage and refrigerate overnight.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, then break into pieces.
Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Place bacon, onion, sauerkraut, stewed tomatoes and sugar in casserole and stir to blend.
Sprinkle with cheese. With lid on casserole, bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream pancakes
directions: Combine and beat flour, salt, baking powder, sugar and milk. Add egg and beat.
Add sour cream and beat.
Drop soda on top of mixture.
Drop vinegar on top of soda and beat.
Bake on greased griddle 1 1/2 minutes on each side or until brown.

title: jewel salad
directions: Dissolve each package of jello with 1 1/2 cups of boiling water.
Place in separate containers and chill.
Combine 1 cup pineapple juice with 1/4 cup sugar.
Heat mixture until it begins boiling.
Remove from stove and mix one box lemon Jell-O, until syrupy.
Combine 2 packages Dream Whip with 1/2 cup cold water and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Whip until stiff.
Fold lemon Jell-O into Dream Whip mixture using low speed on mixer.
Cut Jell-O into squares and fold into lemon Jell-O and Dream Whip mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Mix all ingredients into melted butter and toss lightly.
Make single layer in pan at 400°.
Bake large shrimp for 8 to 10 minutes or small shrimp for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice onions.
Put half in glass pan; cover with crackers and sausage (crumble crackers and sausage).
Put on rest of onions, seasoned salt and cream of mushroom soup.
Bake 40 minutes at 400° covered.
Put on cheese and bake 5 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons butter.
Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain and mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon squares
directions: Pat in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fire and ice pasta
directions: Cut tomatoes, over a bowl to catch the juice, into small pieces.
Coarsely chop the garlic.
Chop the basil leaves, if using fresh basil.
Add the garlic and basil to the tomatoes.
Add salt to taste and a generous amount of black pepper.
Drizzle in the olive oil, adding to your taste.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours, but preferably overnight.
Sauce should be very cold.
About 20 to 30 minutes before serving, begin heating water in a large pot.
When water comes to a rolling boil, add a pinch of salt and the pasta.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes or until it is just tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain pasta well, but do not rinse.
Put pasta in a warm serving bowl.
Immediately add the cold tomato sauce.
Toss well using 2 spoons.
Serve at once.
It's the combination of hot pasta and cold sauce that releases the great flavor.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and drain.
Melt Cheeze Whiz in warm broccoli. Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Bake in covered casserole dish for 40-45 minutes at 375°.
serves 4.

title: peach pie
directions: Make pastry.
Mix sugar, tapioca, salt, lemon juice and almond flavoring.
Combine with peaches.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Place peach mixture in pastry shell.
Dot with butter or margarine. Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican layered sandwich
directions: Place tortilla on a serving platter.
Top with lettuce, half of the turkey and 1 tortilla.
Reserve 1 tablespoon guacamole for top layer; spread remaining guacamole evenly over tortilla. Sprinkle with half of cheese, olives, bell pepper and green onions.
Top with remaining tortilla.
Spread sour cream; sprinkle with remaining cheese, olives, bell pepper and green onions.
Top with guacamole.
Serve immediately.
Serve with salsa.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken parmigiana empanada
directions: Heat butter in saucepan and saute garlic and shallots for one minute.
Add chicken, tomato puree, oregano, basil, wine and pepper to taste.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Correct seasoning, if necessary.
Remove chicken mixture from heat and stir in cheese. Fill empanda disks.
Garnish with grated Parmesan cheese, dried parsley and paprika, if desired, after final egg glaze.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil ingredients well until hard.
Pour over popped corn. Sprinkle with nuts and shape into balls.
Keep hands greased with oleo while shaping into balls.

title: spiced grapes
directions: Weigh and pulp grapes.
Heat pulp over low heat until soft, then run through a colander to remove seeds.
Add 1 cup water to each quart of hulls and cook slowly until tender.
Combine pulp and hulls, add sugar, ground cinnamon, cloves and vinegar.
Boil over low heat 1 hour.
Pour into sterilized jars and process pints at simmering for 20 minutes in hot water bath.
This is delicious with any kind of meat.

title: chicken delight
directions: Oil a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread uncooked rice on bottom of pan.
Mix mushroom soup with water.
Pour over rice.
Lay chicken pieces on top and sprinkle with dry onion soup.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine brown sugar, granulated sugar, salt and cider in large, deep pot.
Tie spices in a piece of cheesecloth and add to cider mixture.
Bring slowly to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve hot in mugs or cups with orange slice floats and cinnamon-stick mullers (stirrers).

title: 3 alarm hot sauce
directions: Cut tomatoes in half.
Take stems off hot peppers.
Put together in pot of boiling water.
Boil until peppers are no longer hard.
Peel tomatoes and put into blender along with peppers.
Put 1/4 cup of the water in blender (for thick sauce, just put 2 teaspoons).
Put spices in and blend. Serve with chips or Mexican food.

title: chutney-almond spread
directions: Allow the cheese to soften; fold in the rest of the ingredients.
Serve with Bremner wafers.
Freezes well.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Makes 2 loaves. Grease pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and green bean dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in large plastic cooking bag.
Add soup, green beans, chicken broth, pepper and 1/2 can of onions to bag.
Shake bag to blend in flour.
Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with remaining onions.
Bake until chicken is tender, 45 to 50 minutes.
Make sure bag has hole in top.

title: grandma's pancakes
directions: Add more flour if not thick enough.
Add more milk if too thick.

title: melt in your mouth hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add egg, buttermilk and water.
Fry to golden brown and serve hot.

title: ritzy chicken
directions: Crush 1 stack of crackers and mix with 1 stick of oleo (melted).
Spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer chicken over crackers.
Mix broth, soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Cover top with 1 stack of crushed crackers.

title: herbed dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, oregano and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Blend in cheese, egg and yeast.
Turn onto well floured surface.
Knead about 5 minutes.
Place in a well-buttered bowl.
Brush top with melted butter.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Shape as desired. Place on buttered baking sheet.
Cover and let rise again until almost doubled.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven 12 to 15 minutes. Serve warm.
Makes 14 to 24 rolls.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Mix chicken, Veg-All and soup together.
Put in baking dish. Mix flour, buttermilk and melted butter together.
Pour over top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: creole-boiled shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp, in large kettle. Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes to allow flavors to blend.
Add shrimp and cook for 3 minutes (it won't quite return to boil).
Remove from heat and add 2 cups of cold water.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain.
For less spicy, replace cayenne pepper with pickling spice.

title: linguine imperial
directions: In large skillet, heat together butter and oil.
Saute garlic, parsley and basil over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in crabmeat and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
In small bowl, combine egg yolks, Parmesan cheese, cream and salt.
In heated serving dish, toss warm linguine with egg mixture.
Add crabmeat mixture and toss gently until combined.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 main dish servings or 6 to 8 side dish servings.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating on medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
The edges will pull away from the pan and the center will be firm to the touch when the cake is done.
Allow the cake to cool enough to be removed from the pan.
Place on the serving tray.
Let cake cool and refrigerate.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and place in blender for 60 seconds.
Grease and flour large pie plate.
Put mixture in pie plate and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Insert knife 1 inch from edge (should come out clean).

title: no-cook mint patties
directions: Blend the corn syrup, butter, extract and salt.
Add sugar; mix with spoon and hands until smooth.
Divide into thirds.
Knead 1 drop red food coloring into one third and 1 drop green food coloring into another third.
Leave remaining third white.
Shape into small balls.
Flatten with fork on waxed paper lined baking sheets.
Let dry several hours.
Makes 72 patties.

title: homemade cranberry sauce
directions: Boil cranberries in 2 cups of water until tender and most have popped (mash while boiling).
Strain through wire colander. Should have 2 tablespoons of pulp left after straining.
Put back into saucepan; add margarine and sugar.
Cook until thick consistency.
Pour into Pyrex or mold sprayed lightly with Pam. Chill until firm.
Garnish with parsley.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter and sugar.
Add flour and eggs. Mix until all ingredients are blended. Pat into a
10 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the pie filling on top, making sure it goes to the edges of the pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
When done, let it cool and the
cut into squares.

title: uncle mike's orange barbecued ribs
directions: Heat grill.
Mix barbecue sauce, juice, peel and pepper. Place ribs, bone side down, on greased grill over low coals. Grill, uncovered, 30 minutes on each side.
Brush with barbecue mix.
Continue grilling 30 minutes or until cooked through.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground chuck, onions, and green peppers.
Drain well. Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
