Add the meat mixture.
Stir well.
Pour into a greased 9x13 baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30-40 minutes.

title: mystery chocolate pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes, peel and mix with margarine.
Add sugar. Sift flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder together.
Add to potato mixture.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat well.
Add vanilla. Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until crust begins to brown.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add pineapple and juice. Add frozen strawberries and stir to unthaw berries.
Put half mixture in glass dish and set in refrigerator to set.
Leave rest of mixture out.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: rich brownies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together; add flour and nuts.
Stir in butter and chocolate.
Place batter in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together 2 cups flour, powdered sugar and margarine.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Smash crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Cook sausage and crumble over crescent rolls.
Sprinkle hash browns over sausage. Cover dish and refrigerate overnight.

title: mom's peanut butter candy
directions: Butter sides of saucepan.
Combine the first 4 ingredients and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Beat until it begins to hold shape.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cool and cut.

title: ratatouille
directions: Chop zucchini, eggplant, onion and green pepper.
Heat oil in skillet and fry onion and garlic for 5 minutes.
Stir in peppers, zucchini and eggplant.
Add the can of tomatoes and basil, mixing well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add the wine and cook for an additional 15 minutes.
Serve over rice. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: fish and chips
directions: Heat oil ( 2 to 3 minutes) in deep hot fryer or kettle to 375°.
Prepare French fried potatoes, allowing 1 potato for each person.
Keep warm.
Dry fish fillets.

title: crab mornay
directions: Make
thick
cream sauce of butter, flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Into
greased baking dish, place layer of crabmeat and
a layer of cheese.
Pour in some cream sauce and continue until dish
is
filled.
Bake
in
moderate oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: throw together chicken casserole
directions: Place layer of stuffing in bottom of baking dish.
Put layer of chicken pieces on top of stuffing mix.
Put a layer of sliced onions on top of that.
Put layer of cheese, followed by layer of broccoli.
Cover with remainder of stuffing mix.
Combine soups together and pour over mix.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: pudding cake
directions: Combine margarine, flour and nuts.
Press into bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
Blend one cup Cool Whip with cream cheese and spread over cooled crust.
Combine both puddings with the milk following the directions on the package.
Put this over cream cheese mixture. Follow with the rest of the Cool Whip.
Top with grated Hershey bar.

title: sugar-free lemon cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Bake pie crusts; set aside to cool.
Bring water to a boil and add gelatin; stir well until dissolved thoroughly.
Add milk to pudding mix; blend well. Add gelatin, Sweet One and cheese to pudding mix and beat with mixer until well blended.
Pour into pie crusts and refrigerate. Makes 2 pies.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Combine milk and pudding in pan and cook according to package directions.
Cool.
Layer half of graham cracker squares in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish, breaking crackers as necessary.
Fold whipped topping into cooled pudding.
Spoon half pudding mixture over first layer of graham crackers.
Spread evenly.
Repeat layer of graham crackers and pudding.
Top with layer of graham crackers and spread frosting evenly over them.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: liver dumplings
directions: Simmer soup bone in water.
Mix the remaining ingredients. Make dumplings and drop into boiling soup broth.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Starter: Given by a friend.

title: edith bennett's refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in lukewarm water and mix in.
Mix together canola oil, warm water, sugar and salt.
Add egg and flour and mix to form stiff dough.
Roll dough 3/8-inch thick.
Cut in circles. Dip both sides in melted margarine or butter and fold one side over other.
Refrigerate or let rise for 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: cranberry-apple sweet potatoes
directions: If using fresh potatoes, cook in large saucepan, covered, in boiling salted water about 15 minutes.
Drain; set aside.
If using canned potatoes, drain and set aside.
Spread pie filling in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange potatoes on top of apples. In small mixing bowl, stir together cranberry sauce and apricot preserves.
Spoon over sweet potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spiced beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
Place beets in fruit jar. Combine vinegar and beet juice; bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Pour over beets; cover jar. Serve very cold.

title: iowa corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch oiled casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cut off fresh corn or use 1 can cream-style corn.
Beat eggs; add sugar and add vanilla.
Add to corn with milk or cream to make a custard consistency.
Bake until firm.
Serve as a vegetable.

title: chocolate wet cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in mixing bowl.
In saucepan, bring to boil margarine, cocoa, shortening and water.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add milk, cinnamon, eggs and vanilla to ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix together and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix margarine, powdered sugar, milk, vanilla, coconut and pecans together thoroughly.
Chill about 2 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and roll into small balls.
Melt paraffin with chocolate chips on low heat.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture and drain on wax paper.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with a variety of fruit.

title: passover bagels
directions: Combine matzoh meal, salt and sugar.
Bring water and margarine to a boil.

Add to matzoh meal combination and mix well. Beat in eggs thoroughly, one at a time or beat eggs together and add a little at a time to matzoh meal combination. Allow mix to stand for about 15 minutes.

title: one egg cake mix
directions: Mix together in order given.
Bake in cupcake tin at 350 for 25 minutes.

title: potpourri
directions: This mixture is great for sweaters or closets.

title: applesauce chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips, 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: german style turkey balls
directions: Mix meats, bread, eggs, onion, 2 tablespoons parsley, lemon juice and seasonings; shape into 2-inch balls.
Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Drop balls into broth.
Simmer, covered, for about 15 minutes.
Remove balls from broth.
Take water and blend in flour.
Blend into broth, stirring until thickened.
Add remaining parsley.
Bring to a boil.
Reheat meat balls in gravy, then stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 6.

title: scalloped onions with cheese sauce
directions: Slice onions thin into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt butter in saucepan. Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in milk; cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth. Add salt and cheese. Cook, stirring, until melted.
Pour over onions.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1
hour.

title: prize chocolate cake
directions: Bake in oven at 350°.

title: aunt rose's sunshine chicken
directions: Wash meat.
Mix all ingredients together.
Baste 2 to 3 times. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers.
Slice very thinly.
Place in a large, shallow, nonmetallic bowl.
Salt generously.
Place a heavy plate on top; weight with jars or cans.
Let stand for 1 hour.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in covered casserole.
Cover. Bake at 275° for 5 or more hours, until beef is tender.
Stir several times; add water if begins to dry out.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together; set aside.
Bring the last 4 ingredients to a boil.
Cool.
Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate overnight.

title: homemade chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool and debone.
Mix flour, milk and margarine well.
Line baking dish with chicken first.
Drain vegetables and layer on top of chicken, then add chicken soup and broth.
Final layer is flour, milk and margarine beaten with wire whisk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in an 8 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 450° approximately 1 hour or until done.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening over warm water; cool slightly. Mix together eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Blend in chocolate mixture, then flour.
Fold in walnuts.
Turn into a well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
(Brownies should still be soft.)
Cut into 20 bars.

title: potato soup
directions: Bring potatoes, celery, onion, pepper and salt to boil. Boil until potatoes are almost done. Add the soup and stir until smoothed in. In another saucepan, melt butter; add seasoned flour to form roux. Stir into soup. Add half and half. Heat to simmer, but do not boil. Garnish with bacon bits or crumbled bacon.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter and add flour to thicken.
Mix all together the rest of ingredients and cook on low until warm.

title: gooey bread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Cut up the loaf of frozen dough into 1-inch cubes.
Put the dough in a Bundt cake pan.
Add the dry mixture to the bread dough.
Pour the oleo over the bread dough and the dry mixture.
Cover; let rise overnight. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until brown.
Dump out on platter and pull apart.

title: two shoo-fly pies
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and shortening like pie dough for crumbs.
Take out 2 cups of these crumbs for top of pies.
To remainder of crumbs in bowl, add eggs, molasses or syrup and 1 1/2 cups hot water from faucet.
Mix well.
Dissolve baking soda in 1/2 cup hot water from faucet.
Add to other liquid mixture. Divide liquid into two unbaked pie shells.
Put crumbs on top. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Turn down oven to 375° and bake for about 30 minutes or until top is dry and done.

title: caramel pie
directions: In mixing bowl, blend cream sheese and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread half into pie crust.
Drizzle with half of caramel topping.
Combine coconut and pecans.
Sprinkle half over the caramel.
Repeat layers.
Chill or freeze until serving.

title: shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, beat the butter with the vanilla until smooth.
Gradually add the sugar and beat for about 5 minutes until smooth.
Continue beating while adding the flour, about 1/4 cup at a time until completely incorporated. Turn out onto a lightly floured surface and knead for 3 minutes until smooth balls form.

title: caramel corn in a bag
directions: In a 4-cup plus glass bowl put butter, brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes, stirring twice while cooking.
Add soda and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour over popped corn in a large paper grocery sack.
Microwave on High one minute.
Shake. Microwave on High one more minute.	Shake.	Microwave on High for 30 seconds.
Shake, eat and enjoy!

title: tomato-opal basil salad
directions: Combine first seven ingredients.
Line dish with French sorrel leaves.
Arrange tomatoes and cheese in rows.
Pour dressing over. Cool.
Garnish with opal basil sprigs.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Roll chicken breasts in Pepperidge Farm stuffing that has been ground fine.
Place in large flat pan.

title: simply delicious dessert
directions: Blend all ingredients; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Cool; remove from pan.

title: nita's clams casino
directions: Mix and bake at 450° for 8 minutes.

title: buttery pancake syrup
directions: Beat Butter Buds into syrup until well blended (Butter Buds will not be dissolved).
Transfer to a saucepan and simmer until Butter Buds dissolve, stirring constantly.
Or, may heat in microwave until Butter Buds have dissolved.
Add cinnamon and mix well.
Serve over pancakes, waffles or French toast.

title: three day iceberg cucumber pickles
directions: First
Day:
7:00 a.m.	Weigh 7 pounds large cucumbers; peel, remove
seeds
and cut into long sticks.
Soak in 2 1/2 cups lime mixed with 2 gallons of water.
Soak 24 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Form into 2 balls and roll in chopped nuts.

title: green and gold squash
directions: Place onion, squash and carrots in boiling water for 5 minutes only.
Drain.

title: mudd slide
directions: Combine butter, flour and nuts.
Mix well and press in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
In medium size bowl combine cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Fold in 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Spread over baked crust.
Combine chocolate and vanilla puddings with cold milk; beat until thick and creamy. Pour over cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and grated chocolate bar.
Chill.

title: cajun pickles(yields 64 servings)
directions: Drain all liquid from pickles.
Pour sugar, garlic and Tabasco sauce into jar on top of pickles.
Shake occasionally for next 3 days.
Refrigerate after the third day.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, reserving a little of the cheese to sprinkle on the top.
Place in a large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: jennifer's hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.
Use 3 tablespoons of this mixture in a mug of hot water.
Marshmallows can be added, if you like.

title: white chocolate peppermint pieces
directions: Melt the white chocolate bark in microwave on high.
Stir every minute or so until the white chocolate is melted completely. Stir in the peppermint pieces.
Spread mixture on to a waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Place candy filled cookie sheet in the freezer until solid.
Once solid, break the candy into pieces. Store in tightly sealed container.

title: creamed corn with chili peppers casserole
directions: Mix in greased casserole.
Bake at 350°
for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: fresh fruit dip #3
directions: Combine flour, sugar, juice and egg.
Cook on low heat until thickened.
Pour hot mixture over cream cheese.
Chill before serving.
Serve with your favorite fruits: red or green apples (sliced), grapes, fresh pineapple, strawberries, etc.

title: lace cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Add egg, oatmeal and salt. Drop by half teaspoonfuls onto buttered pan and bake in 350° oven. After removing from oven, let stand for 1 minute before taking cookies from pan.
This will prevent them from breaking.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; cook 1 1/2 minutes (count minutes after it starts to boil).
Remove from heat.
Add last ingredients.
Stir good.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: pork chops with grilled pineapple
directions: In a dish, combine dressing, juice, sugar and soy sauce.
Add chops; turn to coat.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator, turning occasionally, 3 hours or overnight.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Dump into crock-pot and stir.
Cook on high 3 1/2 to 5 hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll in 1/2-inch balls and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serves 30 people.

title: lemon delite salad
directions: Mix with Jell-O mixture and sprinkle lightly with chopped pecans.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.
Three fat grams per 1/2 cup serving.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add vanilla and stir in eggs one at a time.
Add flour and nuts.
Spread 3/4 of batter in ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with cherry pie filling.
Drop remaining batter by spoonful on filling and spread a little, but let some filling show through.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: four-day bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal and buttermilk; let stand until buttermilk is absorbed, about 3 minutes.
Beat in eggs and oil.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until flour is moistened.
Cover tightly and refrigerate up to 4 days.
Spray muffin pans with Vegalene and fill cups full, but not overflowing.
Bake at 350° in black oven for approximately 25 minutes.
(Brown in convection oven if needed.) Cool and store in covered container.

title: creamy vegetable chowder
directions: Prepare vegetables, cutting zucchini, carrots and celery into small thin strips or pieces.
Combine with onion and chicken broth in a 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to boiling, lower heat and simmer just until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes. Add corn and milk.
Heat to simmering.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and cook squash until tender; drain.
Mix beaten egg with softened butter and add to squash along with other ingredients.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake at 350° until bubbling around the edges about 20 to 30 minutes.
Good!

title: "shoney's strawberry pie"
directions: Cook sugar, flour and water until thickens.
Add Jell-O after removing from stove.
Cool.
Place strawberries in pie shell, then pour Jell-O mixture over strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.
Place strawberries on top of Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressing and cheese.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly and chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sarah's apple pie
directions: Sprinkle flour on crust.
Put flour side down in pie plate. Add apples.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top. You can use as much as you like.
Sprinkle flour on top.
Put top crust on, sealing edges and crimping.
Beat egg white.
Run on top of pie.
Cut 4 slits in crust.
Cook in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes.
For a la mode, add Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: ham delights
directions: Slice open rolls.
Place bottoms in pan. Combine margarine, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and poppy seed.
Spread this on both sides of rolls. Add ham, cheese and onion to bottom.
Replace tops.
Wrap in foil and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool slightly; poke holes in brownies and pour Kahlua over top.
Prepare pudding according to package directions. Crumble entire pan of brownies.
In glass serving bowl, place in layers 1/2 of each of the following ingredients:
crumbled brownies, pudding, candy, nuts and Cool Whip.
Repeat all layers, ending with Cool Whip.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve heaping portions in bowls with large serving spoon.
Serves 12.

title: easy fondue gratin
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Bring wine and thyme to a boil in a saucepan and boil until wine has reduced to approximately 1 cup, about 5 minutes.
Remove about 1/4 of wine and stir into cornstarch until it dissolves.
Stir cornstarch mixture back into pan of wine and boil, stirring constantly, 1 minute.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
Meanwhile, grate cheese.
Crush garlic and rub it on bottom and sides of 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cut bread into 1-inch cubes cutting so there is some crust on each piece.
In large frying pan, melt butter with oil over medium heat.
Add bread.
Toss to distribute butter and oil; saute until golden.
Put about 2/3 of bread cubes in prepared pan.
Stir wine mixture into grated cheese and pour over bread.
Spread remaining bread on top.
Bake until cheese is bubbling, 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: apricot surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With clean hands, mix butter, 1/2 cup sugar, flour and egg yolks until well mixed.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake until light brown, 25 to 30 minutes. Spread apricot filling on hot layer.
Beat egg whites with 3/4 cup sugar.
Spread on top of filling and sprinkle with finely chopped nuts.
Bake in 350° oven until light brown.
Cool 15 minutes before cutting.
Serves lots.

title: spinach vegetable dip
directions: Press spinach into strainer to remove as much liquid as possible.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well 4 to 6 hours before serving.
Cut circle on top of round loaf of rye bread.
Scoop or tear out center of loaf to form a bowl.
Fill with dip mixture.
Serve with torn bread, additional rye bread, crackers or vegetables to dip.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onions in oleo.
Mix broccoli, rice, Cheez Whiz and soup. Pour oleo and onions into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, adding the broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon cheese dip
directions: Make in layers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cover over medium heat until thick.
Baste chicken or ribs.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Butter a pie plate.
Fill 3/4 full with peeled, sliced apples. Melt margarine.
Set aside to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients. Add melted butter or margarine to batter.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Add Cheez Whiz and undiluted soup to rice.
Pour boiling water over broccoli and drain.
Saute onions and celery in oleo.
Combine all ingredients in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: apple pizza pie
directions: For the crust, mix the flour, salt, shortening, Cheddar cheese and ice water.
Place in pan such as a cookie sheet or pizza pan.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Place flour, salt, pepper and paprika in plastic bag.
Line cookie sheet (9 x 13 x 1/2-inch) with aluminum foil.
Melt butter on cookie sheet (in 325° oven).
Coat chicken in plastic bag and then place on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Turn pieces once.

title: san francisco stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add beef; cook and stir until no longer pink.
In a small bowl, combine jelly, cornstarch and mustard; blend well.
Add jelly mixture and vegetables to meat.
Cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.
Serve over rice, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies.
(Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.)
Mix crumbs and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar with mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip (reserve enough for top).
Spread mixture on crumbs and chill 30 minutes.
Mix pudding with 2 1/2 cups milk.
Spread on cream cheese layer.
Chill one hour.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.

title: ginger ale and sherbet punch
directions: Mix together. Serves 25.

title: two crust pie crust
directions: Measure flour and salt into a bowl.
Cut in shortening. Sprinkle water, 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing until all flour is moistened.
Gather dough into 2 balls. Roll out on a floured plastic wrap paper.

title: hot and spicy spinach
directions: Spray large skillet with nonstick cooking spray; heat over medium heat. Add bell pepper and garlic; cook and stir 3 minutes. Add spinach; cook and stir 3 minutes or until spinach begins to wilt. Stir in mustard, lemon juice and pepper flakes. Serve immediately.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour in casserole and bake 30 minutes, covered, in 350° oven. Serve over noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: buttered scott apple dumplings
directions: Measure sifted flour; add baking powder, salt and 3 tablespoons sugar and sift again.
Cut shortening into sifted ingredients until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Add milk, mixing until soft dough is formed.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown together ground beef, onions and garlic.
Drain.
Mix Mozzarella cheese, eggs, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper in a bowl. Cook shells in boiling water 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain. Mix meat mixture with cheese mixture.
Fill shells with 1 tablespoon of mixture.
Place a thin layer of spaghetti sauce in bottom of two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Place stuffed shells in pan. Cover with balance of sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix cookie mix and brown sugar in a bowl.
Mix egg, milk and vanilla with a fork.
Add to bowl and stir until well blended.
Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop by level tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: spanish franks
directions: Brown franks in large skillet.
Remove from pan.
Melt shortening.
Add green peppers, onion and rice.
Brown, stirring occasionally, over high heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: butter horns(sweet)
directions: Cut butter into flour with fingertips.
Add 1 egg yolk and sour cream; mix well.
When blended, shape into ball.
Sprinkle with flour.
Wrap well in waxed paper and chill in refrigerator for several several hours.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils in cold water and drain.
Add lentils to 4 quarts of cold water.
Add all ingredients except olive oil.
Cook on medium heat for 1 hour.
Add 1 cup cooked rice or macaroni.
Add olive oil.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Combine flour, salt, and dash of pepper in a bowl.
Coat pork chops with flour mixture.
Brown in greased skillet.
Combine remaining ingredients to flour mixture.
Pour on chops, cover, simmer 45 minutes.

title: bubble recipe
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use bubble wands, empty spools, bottomless paper cups, berry baskets, etc. to blow bubbles.
Food coloring may be added to the mixture to make an interesting art project by catching the bubbles on a sheet of white paper.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion, following directions on taco seasoning.
Drain; set aside.
Make salad with remaining salad ingredients.
Add grated cheese and olives.
Add hamburger meat. Mix in bag of Fritos corn chips; add dressing.
Mix and serve.

title: mexican corn bread beef meal
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in small amount of oil.
Add ground beef and brown.
Season with chili powder, salt and catsup. Stir in canned corn.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook 5 to 6 hours, stirring every 45 minutes. When removing lid, do not let collected water fall back in. Toward the end of cooking time, you can remove the lid so it will thicken. I set it on a cookie sheet or paper bag to collect splattering and make clean-up easier.

title: old-fashioned fruitcake
directions: Combine fruits and nuts with molasses and grape juice.
Cream margarine and brown sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time; add to fruit mixture.
Sift flour with salt, baking soda and spices and stir into fruit and egg mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour batter into two well-greased loaf pans or a tube pan that has been lined with greased foil.
Bake at 275° for about 2 1/2 hours (about 4 1/2 hours in a tube pan) or until toothpick inserted in cakes comes out clean.
Check often but do not underbake.
Cool cake thoroughly.
Peel off foil from tube cake before wrapping in a cloth moistened with wine or grape juice.

title: mozzarella bread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spread on slices of French bread.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crumble 1 package of crackers in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Slice 3/4 stick of margarine over crackers.
Layer chicken chunks over margarine.
Layer sliced water chestnuts over chicken. Blend soups and sour cream together and spread over top.
Top with 1 package of finely crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter
in baking dish.
Beat eggs and sugar until creamy, add milk, vanilla, flour and corn.	Pour melted butter into mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients and make very small balls, lightly coat with cornstarch and fry in oil until browned on both sides.

title: sour cream jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pineapple (not drained). Stir well and cool in the refrigerator for a few minutes.
Place sour cream in same bowl.
Stir and add nuts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: dressing
directions: In a frying pan, saute margarine, onion and celery.
Add to first ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: take-a-dip
directions: Combine yogurt, sour cream and soup mix.
Let set overnight. Serve with sliced vegetables.

title: mexican sweat
directions: Mix together Ro-Tel, all soups and peppers.
Brown meat and onions.
Mix with soup mixture.
Layer in baking pan: Doritos, meat mixture, grated cheese and ending with cheese on top.
Make at least 2 layers.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: louisiana red beans and rice(2 to 3 servings)
directions: Slice sausage or kielbasi into small rounds.
Braise in small amount of water at low heat.
Dice onion, celery and green pepper; add minced garlic.
Then add to meat.
Add red kidney beans with liquid.
Add basil and thyme.
If desired, to taste, add Tabasco sauce.
Finally, add cooked rice.
Cook mixture over low heat for another 30 minutes.

title: fish fritters
directions: Mash fish.
Beat egg yolks until light and thick.
Add flour, salt, pepper, garlic and parsley to fish.
Add egg whites, beaten to a froth.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot deep fat (360° to 370°).
Fry until brown.
Serves 4.

title: german goulash
directions: Combine all the ingredients, juice also. Bring to a boil, turn down heat and simmer. Put oven
350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve with salad and home made rolls.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour with pumpkin pie spice.
Add chopped apples, chopped nuts and seedless raisins.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake in 9 x 13 greased pan (or loaf pan) for about 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve plain or with whipped cream or with icing.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, walnuts and oleo.
Pat into bottom of baking pan (13 x 9-inch approximate size).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Mix softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Mix well and place on top of crust.
Mix pudding with milk.
Put on top of cream cheese mixture.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip. (I usually put the Cool Whip on top just before serving.)
Keep refrigerated.

title: jello salad
directions: Beat the cream cheese in juice while hot.
Add Jell-O, hot water, then nuts and pineapple last. Fold in Dream Whip when cooled.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil for 5 minutes the brown sugar, syrup, salt and oleo. Remove from heat.
Add soda and cream of tartar.
Pour over popcorn.
Stir for four minutes on cookie sheet or in shallow pan. Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir 2 or 3 times while baking.
Put in container and seal.
Keeps very good.
(So nice and crisp.)

title: easy quiche
directions: Grease a 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Spread broccoli or spinach or asparagus in plate.
Beat sour cream, cottage cheese, baking mix, margarine and eggs until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high).
Pour into plate.
Top with tomato and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean (about 40 minutes).
Cool 5 minutes and serve. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: asparagus bake
directions: Drain asparagus and place in shallow 1-quart baking dish. Combine mayonnaise with red pepper, cheese and onions. Fold in egg white. Spread over asparagus. Bake at
350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate marshmallow candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients 6 minutes after it comes to a rapid boil.
Take off stove.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Beat.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes about five pounds.
Use peanut butter chips to make peanut butter fudge.

title: dip
directions: Mix all of the preceding ingredients together good.

title: carrot coin salad
directions: Heat soup, sugar, vinegar and oil to a boil.
Pour sauce over vegetables and let stand 4 to 8 hours.
Serve chilled.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Line with white bread. Top with chopped green onions, chopped ham, Cheddar cheese and green chilies.
Add another layer of white bread.
Pour 1 quart of milk, beaten with 6 eggs, over top.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour with no cover.

title: super strawberry ice cream
directions: Slice and puree 1 pint strawberries with lemon juice in a blender or food processor.
Beat eggs and sugar until thick and lemon colored.
Beat in cream.
Stir in pureed strawberries. Process in an ice cream maker.
Fold in additional strawberries after ice cream is processed but while it is still soft.
For firmer ice cream, refreeze.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: fancy, easy pork tenderloin
directions: Season pork generously with garlic salt and pepper.
Put flour in baking bag and shake.
Place pork in baking bag.
Put carrots and mushrooms between pork halves in bag.
Close bag with a twistie and put 6 small slits in top of bag.
Put bag in baking pan.
Cook at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6. Very good served with Cowboy Rice.

title: hungarian chicken
directions: Coat chicken with salt, pepper and paprika; brown
chicken. Also sprinkle chicken with garlic and saute onion.
Put in broth. Cook chicken in covered pan for 1/2 hour until tender (simmer low).
Take chicken out to make gravy.
Thicken with flour and water to make gravy.

title: broccoli salad and dressing
directions: Cut broccoli (florets and tender part of stock) into small bite size pieces and combine with sunflower seeds, raisins and bacon in bowl.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, pudding, sour cream and Cool Whip, saving 1/3 Cool Whip.
Put alternate layers of wafers, bananas and mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: maravian slaw
directions: Boil together the first 3 ingredients.
Set aside to cool. When this dressing is cool, pour over other ingredients.
Mix good and refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
It is good as long as you keep refrigerated in a tight container.
I like the green sweet peppers in mine.

title: rare roast beef
directions: Place in shallow pan.
No cover, no water.
Roast "must be room temperature."
For each pound of roast, take 1 hour per pound and let stand, example, 7 pound roast would stand for 7 hours on counter.
Preheat oven to 425°.
For a 5 pound roast, cook 35 minutes.
Add 5 minutes per pound.
After cooking time leave in oven for 3 hours with oven off.
Once you put roast in oven do not open oven door until ready to serve.

title: sauteed bay scallops
directions: Place scallops in a bowl.
Add vermouth, garlic, salt and pepper and mix well.
Let stand for 1 hour, then drain well.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Roll scallops in bread crumbs and shake off excess.
Melt butter over fairly high heat and saute scallops 2 minutes until golden.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Serve immediately with lemon wedges.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots until barely tender.
Drain.
Cook onion gently in 1/2 cup butter.
Stir in flour, salt and mustard.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Add pepper, celery salt and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Place carrots in shallow casserole dish. Pour cheese sauce over carrots and top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sugar-free fruit muffins
directions: Beat egg, then add buttermilk, soda and Sweet 'N Low.
Add Bisquick; stir until just moist, then add fruit.
If using canned fruit, drain it well.
If using frozen fruit, thaw before adding to batter.
Bake about 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: crab party spread
directions: Blend crab and cocktail sauce and pour over cheese. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: yummy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix everything together except ketchup and cook until thickened, then stir in ketchup.

title: microwave seafood puffs(convection)
directions: Remove ceramic tray.
Place wire rack in upper position of oven and preheat oven to 380°.

title: hot and spicy warm-up
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and simmer for 5 minutes. This makes a delicious hot and spicy warm-up.
Serves 5.

title: pinwheel cookies
directions: Combine dates, sugar and water and cook over low heat for 10 minutes. Stir in nuts and cool. Cream the last 6 ingredients together and divide the dough in half. Roll one out and spread with half of the date nut mix. Roll up like jelly roll and do the same with the other half. Freeze until firm, then slice and bake in oven at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: chilled strawberry pie
directions: Puree about 2 cups strawberries in blender.
Slice the rest. Reserve 3 for garnish.
In saucepan, combine sugar, gelatin, salt, water and lemon juice.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
Add pureed strawberries; cool thoroughly.
Fold sliced strawberries and Kirsch into gelatin mixture.
Whip 1/2 cup of the cream; gently fold into gelatin mixture.
Pour into crust.
Chill for 3 hours or until firm.
Add cream just before serving.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and drain.
Place in casserole.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over and dot with butter.
Cover with slices of the cheese.
Cover with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all the salad ingredients in a large bowl.

title: brownies
directions: Melt stick of butter in pan.
Mix reminder of ingredients together.
Pour melted butter into mixture.
Mix well and pour back into pan.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: hash browns and cheese casserole
directions: Place hash browns in lightly buttered 2-quart casserole. Combine next 5 ingredients and pour over hash browns.
Sprinkle with crushed corn flakes and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: herbed garlic butter
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter or margarine over low heat. Stir in garlic, oregano and vinegar.
Good on green beans, asparagus, whole kernel corn and peas.
Yield:
1/4 cup.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef until done, stirring to break up into small pieces.
Drain well on paper towels.
Salt and pepper lightly. Allow to cool.
Combine beef, beans, taco mix, onions, chilies, tomatoes and olives.
Put lettuce in large bowl; add beans and beef mixture.
Sprinkle on cheese and taco chips.
Pour dressing over all and toss well when you are ready to serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or 3 coffee cans.
Mix the sugar, oil, eggs, pumpkin and water.
Sift dry ingredients and spices.
Add to pumpkin mixture with raisins and nuts.
Fill loaf pans or coffee cans 2/3 full. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Let stand a few minutes. Remove from cans and wrap in foil.
Replace in can with lid on and refrigerate or freeze for gift giving.

title: icing cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at
350° for 10 minutes.
When cool, ice cookies as desired.

title: dark chocolate cake(no eggs used)
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa, salt
and
baking soda.
Bring the coffee to a boil and stir it gently into the matter.
Mixture will be soupy.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes. Contains approximately 185 calories per serving.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, combine uncooked rice mix with seasonings, celery, mushrooms and water; dot top with 1/4 cup butter.
Arrange chicken over rice.
Brush with melted butter.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour; uncover, and bake 30 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Toss oil into noodles.
Spray crock-pot with Pam cooking spray.
Mix all the remaining ingredients with noodles.
Put in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Fifteen minutes before serving, sprinkle 1 cup of cheese on top.

title: ham with cider glaze
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Score ham with diagonal cuts in a diamond pattern.
Place ham on a rack in a shallow roasting pan. Insert a meat thermometer; bake ham until thermometer registers 140° (about 2 hours).
Meanwhile, in a large saucepan combine cider, honey, vinegar, mustard, and chili powder.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Boil gently, uncovered, about 15 minutes, stirring frequently (watch carefully, as mixture will bubble up). You should have about 2 cups of mixture.
Remove half of the mixture to a small bowl. Stir in butter and 1/4 teaspoon of the pie spice; set aside for sauce.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix margarine, 4 tablespoons of sugar and flour well.
Press into bottom of jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash, trim and cut squash; boil in salted water until tender. Drain and add celery soup, sour cream, butter, onion and all but 1/2 cup of cornbread stuffing.
Mix well and put into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice the beef across the grain into bite-size strips.
Cook the beef in a large skillet over high heat in 1 tablespoon of the hot cooking oil about 1 to 2 minutes or to desired doneness of meat.
Remove meat from the skillet.
Add remaining oil, mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Stir in the water, catsup, instant bouillon granules and pepper. Combine the flour and sour cream and add to the mixture in the skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Return meat to skillet.
Heat through.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 2.

title: cooked dressing
directions: Add first three ingredients. Mix well with an electric mixer, slowly add vinegar and cook over medium heat until starts to thicken.
Can be used for chicken salad or potato salad.

title: breakfast nog
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and mix until frothy.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in coffee can 1/2 to 3/4 full. May add raisins or nuts if desired.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: ham in sour cream
directions: Cook ham and onion in butter until onion is tender but not brown.
Sprinkle with flour; gradually stir in sour cream.
Add mushrooms.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture thickens.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain; arrange in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mile high biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, cream of tartar and salt. Cut in shortening with fork until all particles are fine.
Add egg and milk all at once.
Stir until dough clings together in a ball.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix well and freeze in a 9 x 13-inch covered dish.
Cut in squares when ready to serve.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sprinkle salt on potatoes; sift flour. Cut shortening and potatoes into flour. Add milk gradually. Mix well and roll out onto floured area. Cut with biscuit cutter. Put on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. Remove from oven and butter tops. Serve. Makes about 12 biscuits.

title: pineapple cream cheese cake
directions: Bake at 350°
in 9 x 13-inch dish that has been greased and floured.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup in beans and some of the onions in soup.
Put remaining onion rings on top.
Bake until heated, about 30 minutes.

title: mini cherry topped cheesecakes
directions: Preheat
oven
Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter.	Press equal portions into 18 paper-lined muffin cups.
In a large bowl beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs
and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spoon into prepared cups.
Bake 20 minutes. Cool;
then chill for 10 to 20 minutes.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Makes 18.

title: sober cider
directions: Mix cider and juice together and serve warm in mugs.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Serve with a cinnamon stick.

title: gourmet cheese bread
directions: Slice bread lengthwise.
In a bowl, mix mayonnaise, cheese and onions.
Spread on bread.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Broil for only a minute or two if the cheese has not melted.

title: bacon and egg salad
directions: Cook bacon until
crisp.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of fat. Mix broken salad
greens
and
other
salad ingredients.
Toss with bacon fat, then add dash of vinegar.
Add salt and pepper to taste and toss again.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: owen's cornbread dressing
directions: Brown ground meat in a heavy pot.
(You may want to remove excess fat at this point.)
Add onions, celery and garlic. Cook until these vegetables are tender.
Put giblets in a separate pot with water to cover. Simmer until tender.

Be sure the giblets are finely chopped, then add to meat mixture. Add 2 cups liquid which may be water, the broth from boiling the giblets or other broth. Add shallots, bell pepper, parsley and oysters.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add water when needed to keep moist.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Crumble cornbread into the meat mixture and mix well.
May be garnished with parsley and sliced hard-cooked eggs.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and keep warm.
In large saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sour cream, heavy cream, cheese, chives, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Cook over low heat until hot and bubbly.
Add noodles.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 or more.

title: wackie cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix wet ingredients and add to dry ingredients.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° in a square cake pan.

title: crunchy french toast
directions: Trim crusts from bread; cut slices lengthwise into rectangles. Reconstitute dried egg.
Dip bread slices into egg, then into cereal.
Fry until golden brown in lightly greased skillet or griddle over campfire or on grill over medium coals.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: rum pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk and flavorings; beat well.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple apricot bread
directions: Pour boiling water over apricots and let stand for 15 minutes. Remove apricots from water and add milk to the water to make 2/3 cup in all.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and allspice.
Cream together the sugar and shortening.
Beat in the egg.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the liquid.
Fold in fruit and walnuts.
Spoon into a greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool on rack.

title: patti's vidalia onion dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until golden and bubbly. Serve with crackers (best with Triscuits).
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.

title: reese cups
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter and sugar together.
Add vanilla and mix with hand.
Melt chocolate and wax in double boiler.
Shape dough into balls and dip into chocolate.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Put chopped onion in the bottom of the crock pot. Layer with browned beef, sliced potatoes, and beans. Spread tomatoes or soup over top. Sprinkle the seasoning as desired. Cover and cook on low 7-9 hours. Serves 4-6.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: *If not using self-rising flour, reduce flour to 1/2 cup and add 1/8 teaspoon of salt and 1/8 teaspoon of baking powder.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry for 9-inch, two-crust pie as directed on package.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: After creaming sugar and margarine, add other ingredients. Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Turn down to 350° until done (pie doesn't wiggle) about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli pierre
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place uncooked broccoli in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Mix onions, soup, sour cream and Parmesan cheese. Spread over broccoli. Top with bread crumbs. Bake for 35 minutes or until broccoli is just tender. Serves 6 to 8.

title: friendship applesauce
directions: Wash, peel, core and slice the apples.
Place in electric frypan on low/medium heat.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cook until mushy. Add the cinnamon and brown sugar to taste. Share with friends and family!
Enjoy.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter.
Boil chicken, save juice.
Combine all can goods and spices.
Debone chicken and add to canned good mixture.
Boil tortillas in chicken juice for 5 minutes.
Then put layer in pan, followed by layer of chicken mix. Put cheese slices on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken or turkey strata(low-fat)
directions: Place the cubes of bread on bottom of a 12 x 8-inch nonstick pan.

Combine the chicken, onion, celery, chilies, mayonnaise, salt and pepper in a medium-sized bowl and spoon over the bread cubes. Tear tortillas into bite-sized pieces and place them on top of the chicken mixture.
Combine the eggs, milk, cottage cheese and soup in a small bowl and pour over the top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight to allow the flavors to blend.

Preheat oven to 325° and bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour or until the dish is firm and set. Remove from the oven and let stand for 10 minutes before serving. Serves 8. Contains 328 calories per serving.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a shallow bowl, beat together eggs, milk, vanilla and cinnamon.
Dip bread into egg mixture, coating both sides (if using French bread, let soak in egg mixture about 30 seconds on each side).

title: cornbread
directions: Stir it up.
Put it in a pan.
Put it in the oven or on top of stove.
In oven 55°.
On stove 20°.
Turn it over.
Wait 2 minutes and it is done.

title: egg cheese brunch casserole(serves 12)
directions: Place half of bread cubes in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer 1/2 of the cheese, 1/2 of turkey ham and 1/2 of butter; repeat layers.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Mix all these ingredients together.
Put in a buttered pan (8 x 12-inches).

title: meringue cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding sugar while beating.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop mixture by teaspoons onto cookie sheet that has been lined with brown grocery bag (cut to fit cookie sheet).
Put cookie sheet in oven and turn oven off.
Leave door of oven closed.
Leave cookies in oven overnight and remove in the morning.
Keep in sealed box.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix in usual way.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Saute first three ingredients until onion is clear.
Saute until all red disappears from meat; salt and pepper to taste.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: melt in mouth cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, vanilla and egg; beat until light. Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Combine oats, nuts, brown sugar and margarine.
Mix well. Firmly press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan forming a 1/2-inch rim around edge.
Bake until lightly browned.
Cool. Combine cheese, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla; beat at high speed until well blended.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well.
Pour in crust.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Chill several hours before serving.
Garnish with berries if desired.

title: date cookie
directions: Cook over low heat; heat to a boil. In a bowl, put 2 cups Rice Krispies, nuts and coconut (optional). Pour date mixture into dry ingredients. Cool; roll in balls, then in powdered sugar.

title: date balls
directions: Put dates, butter and sugar into a saucepan and cook until dates dissolve.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts and form into balls. Dip into powdered sugar.

title: cabbage delight
directions: Cut cabbage in small strips; wash and put in large pot and boil for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Put drained cabbage in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix 3 tablespoons milk with cream of chicken soup.
Pour soup over cabbage.
Then pour Cheez Whiz over cabbage and soup.
Don't mix.
Put butter in frying pan and melt; add stuffing mix and stir until coated with butter.
Put buttered stuffing mix over casserole.
Bake at 350° until light brown. Serves 8.

title: texas cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Bring margarine, cocoa and water to a rapid boil; then mix with the dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix all well and pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Boil ribs until tender.
Remove from water.
Place in dish or cooking bag.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Add gelatin to water and set aside.
Boil soup and add cream cheese; stir until melted.
Remove from heat and add mayonnaise. Mix remaining ingredients and pour into a greased mold. Refrigerate overnight.

title: lasagna with meat
directions: Peel and cut up onion.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt. Drain.
Mix sauce and hamburger.
Simmer.
Prepare noodles and cook 10 minutes.
Drain.
Rinse with hot water.
Use 9 x 13-inch baking dish; layer noodles, layer sauce and layer cheese.
Repeat ending top layer with cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Can be frozen.

title: rolled white cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients except the last cup of flour should be reserved for rolling cookies.

Knead dough to desired consistency with the last cup of flour and divide dough to roll to about 1/8-inch thick. Garnish with sugar and cut out cookies in desired shapes. Bake at 300° for about 7 minutes.
Check for doneness. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: taco potatoes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Pour off excess fat. Add taco seasoning, 1 cup water and peppers.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring. Slash tops of each potato and squeeze open.
Spoon taco mixture over potatoes.
Garnish with dairy sour cream and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: casey's favorite chicken
directions: Skin all the chicken pieces and wash thoroughly.
Dip the chicken in the teriyaki sauce and then flour; place in a nonstick, shallow cooking pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from the oven and apply melted margarine or butter with a brush to the dry areas of the chicken.
Place back in the oven and cook for another 30 minutes.
Casey's Favorite Chicken is now ready to eat!

title: cheese and hot dog casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan and heat on stove until bubbly.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Boil the water.
Add to dry ingredients with the oil.
Knead together until well mixed and let cool.
Store in a large Ziploc bag or covered container in refrigerator when not in use.
Can make different colors of play dough by varying the flavor of the Kool-Aid.
It smells great and keeps for a long time!

title: 7 egg pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and shortening until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat.
Add flour and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In
a
heavy kettle, combine all the ingredients except soda. Heat
to a boil and continue cooking until peanuts quit popping and
is turning caramel colored.
Add soda and pour in a large greased jelly roll pan.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: marinated tortellini
directions: Cook tortellini; drain and cool.
Mix as directed the Italian dressing.
Pour dressing, Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes in with tortellini.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir and chill.

title: christmas crunches
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Stir in oats, corn flakes, coconut and pecans.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls and place 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool on wire racks.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: dream cycle cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat with mixer 4 minutes. Pour into two 9-inch cake pans (greased and floured).
Bake 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Let cool and cut layers in half with string.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook onion, carrots, garlic and oleo.
Mix soup to this mixture.
Add sour cream and croutons.
Add the zucchini.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
If desired, sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Put onion and garlic in oil; saut until golden. Put in remaining sauce ingredients and cook 1 1/2 hours. Cook 1 package of shells in boiling salted water until tender.

title: pecan pie cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour evenly into greased muffin pan. Makes 1 dozen. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat 1 inch of vegetable oil to 375 degrees.
Mix corn meal, salt, onions, and baking soda.
Stir in buttermilk.
Once mixed, drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until brown, about 20 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozens.

title: hot chow
directions: Grind all vegetables.
Let come to a boil; boil for 5 minutes. Pack in jars and seal.

title: ham and rice
directions: Heat butter and oil in skillet.
Saute onion, celery and pepper for 3 minutes.
Add ham and mix well.
Saute for 5 minutes. Add rice and cook 2 minutes, until rice is coated.
Add broth and boil over high heat.
Put lid on skillet and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook for 23 minutes (do not lift lid).
Remove lid.
Add parsley and ripe olives.
Toss rice with fork until fluffy.

title: enchilada casserole dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, brown beef and drain well. Prepare Lawry's enchilada sauce according to package directions. Add 8 ounce can tomato sauce to enchilada sauce.
In skillet, add little margarine/butter and turn corn tortillas on both sides until softened and set aside.
Add half of enchilada sauce to ground beef; set rest aside.

title: meatballs and macaroni(makes about 8 servings)
directions: Combine spaghetti sauce and meat balls in medium sauce cooker with a lid over medium heat; let simmer for about 30 to 45 minutes. While the meatballs and sauce are simmering, cook macaroni in a separate sauce pan following instructions on box.
After macaroni is cooked, drain water, turn heat down to low or warm; add milk, butter/cheese stirring frequently.
Allow cheese to melt.
When cheese has melted, remove from stove eye; add to meatballs and sauce.
Remove both from stove top; serve with garlic bread.

title: festive flounder
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place large size (14 x 20-inch) brown-in-bag in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
In medium bowl combine soup, sour cream, water, chives and nutmeg.
Reserve 3/4 cup.
Add rice and 1/4 cup almond to soup mixture.
Mix well. Spoon soup mixture in bag.
Sprinkle flounder with salt; place in bag.
Spoon reserved soup mixture over flounder.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup almonds.
Close bag with twist tie.
Make 6 half-inch slits in top.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes, or until fish flakes easily. Yields 4 servings.

title: creamy beef bake
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed; set aside.
Brown meat and onion in margarine.
Stir in soup and milk.
In a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer half the macaroni and half the meat mixture. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chow mein cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter together.
When melted, stir in chow mein noodles and marshmallows.
Mix well. Spoon tablespoons full onto waxed paper and chill until set.

title: mexican wedding cake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Beat butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy. Add water and vanilla. Gradually add flour and nuts, beating until well mixed. Refrigerate until firm (about 30 minutes). Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes or until lightly brown on bottom. Cool on wire racks for 10 minutes, then roll in remaining 1 cup of powdered sugar. When completely cool, roll again in sugar. Makes 4 dozen.

title: corn flake crisps
directions: Cream together butter and sugars; beat in egg and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in corn flakes, coconut and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until delicately browned.
Cool slightly before removing to cooling rack.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: louisiana gumbo
directions: In a large gumbo pot, make a roux with oil and flour.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until roux is dark caramel color.
Remove from fire and add remaining ingredients, except for 1/2 cup green onions, file and rice.
Boil about 2 hours or until meat is tender and gumbo has thickened.
In the last 15 minutes of boiling, add the rest of the green onions.
Remove from fire and add file.
Serve over hot rice in gumbo bowls.

title: butter crunch toffee
directions: Cook and constantly stir to 300° or until candy smokes. Remove from heat when mixture turns a medium brown in color.
Pour onto cookie sheet covered with tinfoil.
Let cool.
Spread 1 large melted Hershey bar over top and sprinkle with chopped walnuts.

title: one step pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Make a well and add oil and milk. Mix with a spoon or hands until moist.
Spray a 10-inch pie pan with Pam.
Pat dough into pie pan, spreading it evenly.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cream potatoes after cooking with milk and butter Place in baking dish (buttered).
Alternate	each
layer
with
sour cream, leaving top layer
for potatoes.
Cover with cheese and bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine everything in one bowl and mix by hand.
Do not beat! Beat eggs in bowl before adding them.
Pour batter into 4 (1-pound) coffee cans or 2 loaf pans that have been well-greased.
Fill half full and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holiday pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Mix together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Set aside. Combine the pumpkin, oil, sugar and eggs. Mix until well blended. (You can use your mixer also.) Add dry ingredients and mix well. Add by hand the nuts and raisins. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. You can ice them also.

title: english pea and water chestnut casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and celery. Saute until soft.
Remove from heat and add peas and chestnuts. Fold in soup and pimento.
Pour into two-quart casserole. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Marinate quartered cucumbers in vinegar and water mixture. Add salt and diced onion. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

Drain and discard onion. Grate cucumber and drain well again (squeeze as much liquid out as possible). Add to softened cream cheese. Season to taste with mayonnaise, salt and pepper, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce and food coloring.
Spread bread rounds or shapes lightly with soft butter, then cucumber spread.
Layer with damp paper towel in Tupperware and chill.
May be made hours ahead, even a day before.

title: baking dough
directions: Mix enough water with dry ingredients to make a dough.
Make shapes with cookie cutters and bake at 300° for about 1 hour (cook longer if real thick, shorter time if real thin).

title: dorito casserole
directions: Combine ground beef and onion in a heavy skillet.
Brown. Drain off excess fat; add chili powder.
In mixing bowl combine next 5 ingredients.
Add to meat mixture.
Crush Doritos corn chips and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until done. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: fennel-spinach-roquefort and walnut salad
directions: In a salad bowl toss together the fennel, spinach, walnuts and Roquefort.
In a small bowl whisk together the vinegar, salt and pepper to taste, add oils in a slow stream whisking, and whisk the dressing until emulsified.
Drizzle the dressing over the salad and toss it well.

title: honey-butter whip
directions: Combine and cream together butter and honey.
Add whipping cream and whip until fluffy.

title: zucchini bread(skinny bread)
directions: Grate zucchini on coarse side of grater.
(May use a bit more than 2 cups of zucchini but not less.)
Sift dry ingredients into wet mix and stir.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: orange-topped chops
directions: In a skillet, brown pork chops on both sides in oil. Top with oranges; sprinkle with cloves and pepper. Cover and simmer for 35 minutes or until meat juices run clear. Yield: 6 servings.

title: christmas fruit cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, fruit, dates, nuts and chocolate chips.
Stir in dry ingredients. Chill.
Roll in small balls.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven. Makes approximately 4 dozen cookies.
Dough will be stiff on last part.
Do not use hand beater, stir by hand.
If you don't like certain fruits, omit or use raisins or your choice.

title: zesty salmon sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in small saucepan; heat through gently. This can also be heated up in the microwave.
Pour sauce over fish and bake in foil in oven or barbecue.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking soda and cocoa.
Add water, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Don't use mixer for this cake, just blend well.
Pour into greased pan of your choice.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until tests done, also according to the pan used.
Frost with Cool Whip or any frosting of your choice.

title: vanilla milk chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs.
Beat.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburg and onion in a frying pan.
Pour all juice out of pan and add corn and gravy. Stir and cook about 10 minutes. Place mixture in a casserole dish topped with mashed potatoes. Bake about 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry mist
directions: Mix juices; pour into large iced glasses (prefer crushed ice in glasses).
Garnish with lemon slices.
Add vodka, if desired.

title: chicken crescent squares
directions: Tear chicken into pieces.
Mix together with first 6 ingredients. Put two crescent roll triangles together to make a square, spoon about 1/4 cup of mixture into the center of the square.
Fold corners up and seal all sides.
Dip into melted butter, add a little parmesan and garlic to bread crumbs and dip square into bread crumbs.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 8 squares.

title: pork or chicken pasta
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions; drain and set aside (add a little oil to water to prevent sticking).
Slice meat into strips (boneless pork slices or chicken breasts).
Saute in oil until browned.
Add chopped celery, onion, water and soy sauce.
Simmer until meat and vegetables are tender.
Thicken with cornstarch mixed in water.
Stir into cooked and drained linguine.

title: mini pizza
directions: Flatten biscuits with palm of hand. Put 1 teaspoon of your favorite spaghetti sauce on biscuit. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Put pepperonis on top. Bake at 400° until biscuits are done.

title: zucchini salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours before serving.
Keeps up to 2 weeks.

title: cheese ring
directions: *Have cheeses two different colors.

title: chocolate-chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter cookie sheet.
Combine flours, baking soda, baking powder and salt in a medium size bowl.

title: frozen punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Set aside.
Bring sugar and water to boil until completely dissolved.
Add to Jell-O mixture. Add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Mix well and freeze.
Two hours before using, take out of freezer.
After becoming slush, add two bottles of ginger ale.
Serves 50.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown sausage, ground beef, onions and peppers.
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes; simmer.
Add dash of salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Mix all the ingredients.
Put into large, greased baking dish.
Place pepperoni on top and then top with Mozzarella cheese.
Put in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cover with foil the last 15 minutes of baking time.

title: baked rice
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms.
Grease casserole with margarine. Add all ingredients with water last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves four.

title: fish with linguine
directions: Saute onion and garlic for 2 minutes on low heat.
Add tomato puree, bay leaf, parsley, basil, salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

Add fish (cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces) and simmer until fish is white or about 15 minutes. Pour over cooked linguine and sprinkle Pecorino and Romano grated cheese over top and serve. May remove fish from sauce and serve separately over pasta.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl until well blended.
Bake at 350°.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion and noodles in 1/2 cup butter.
Add rice and brown lightly.
Add remaining 1/2 cup butter, stock and salt to rice in pan.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender. Garnish with chives and almonds.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake for 25 or 30 minutes, depending on oven.
Let cool.
Mix 1/2 pint sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Add to cooled pie and bake 5 more minutes.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Add strawberries.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix everything together.
Melt 1/4 stick butter or margarine in an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour in chicken mixture and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon poppy seed.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: striped delight
directions: Mix crumbs with melted butter.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O over cottage cheese.
Stir until dissolved.
Add oranges and pineapple that has been drained.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread mixes as directed.
Let cool.
Crumble bread and mix all ingredients together.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter all together.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Then mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 3 eggs.
Mix this all together and pour or spread over first mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix water and jello; allow to cool. Add strawberries (partially thawed, if frozen) to cooled mixture.

Refrigerate until slightly jelled. Break angel food cake into 50-cent pieces. Mix cake with thickened mixture. Pour into ungreased tube pan and refrigerate. After 3 hours, invert onto plate and frost with Cool Whip.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cut zucchini into small pieces and cook until tender in chicken broth.
Cook onion and garlic in butter until tender. Combine all ingredients in blender, including salt and curry. Serve hot or cold.
Can be frozen.
Yield: 6 to 8 first course servings or 4 servings as a main dish.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Layer as directed (amounts as wished).
Let stand overnight. Stir before serving.

title: banana oatmeal bread
directions: Combine oats and buttermilk; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in bananas and oat mixture.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir into various mixtures.
Spoon into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake about 50 minutes at 350°.
Makes one loaf.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken. Cook rice as directed. Chop chicken. Add soups, sour cream, pecans, broth. Put in 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° until bubbly. GOOD! Serve with salad and bread.

title: tofu-mushroom loaf
directions: Saute first four ingredients.
Mix all remaining ingredients except cheese in large bowl.
Add the onion-mushroom mixture to the tofu mixture, fold gently and spoon into oiled loaf pan.
Top with Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: thelma figgin's ham loaf
directions: Mix first six ingredients and shape into loaf.
Pour mixture of the remaining ingredients over loaf.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven for 2 hours or until browned on top.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, caraway seed and raisins.
Add margarine.
Combine and add buttermilk, egg and baking powder.
Bake in an iron pan in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Brush top with margarine after baking.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix ingredients together in boiler; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and beat with mixer until cool enough to spread on cake.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix hamburger, sausage, rice and onions and roll in cabbage leaves. Place in large kettle and pour tomatoes and catsup over rolls. Cook slow for 2 hours.

title: ricotta pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: holiday cauliflower
directions: Break cauliflower into medium size flowerets.
Cook in boiling water until crisp-tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain well; set aside.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients; shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown meatballs. Heat the cream of mushroom soup and water; pour over meatballs in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Or, pour soup and meatballs into slow cooker and cook on low for 2 to 3 hours.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies as directed on box; cool.
Crumble 1/2 of pan in bottom of a large bowl.
Make 1 package of pudding as directed on box; pour over brownies in bowl.
Let set for a few minutes, then layer Cool Whip over pudding and sprinkle with Heath bar bits. Repeat process with second half of brownies.
Chill.

title: oatmeal-coconut cookies
directions: Cream shortening well.
Add vanilla and sugar; cream well. Add eggs and mix.
Sift salt, soda, baking powder and flour; combine this with coconut and oatmeal.
Mix thoroughly.
Add this to creamed mixture; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon (size of walnut) onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and until center has just fallen, 15 minutes.

title: mushroom soup
directions: In a large skillet, put butter or margarine and melt; add scallions and mushrooms.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes, until tender.
Add flour and cook for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add milk and broth, using whisk to combine well.
Return soup to moderate heat and simmer and stir for 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Bring the syrup, sugar and butter to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter.
Stir in corn flakes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soups, broth and tomatoes.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture in the bottom of a buttered casserole dish.
Add 1/2 the bag of corn chips, 1/2 the onions and 1/2 of the cheese.
Repeat with the other 1/2 of the chicken mixture, then the other half of corn chips, onions and cheese.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Put tomatoes, peppers and onions through food grinder or chop very fine.
Mix with 1 cup salt.
Put in a thin bag and hang to drain for 24 hours.
Then mix thoroughly with vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, celery seed and cayenne pepper.
Do not cook or heat this mixture.
It keeps perfectly with sealing.
Makes about 3 pints.

title: puff paste
directions: Sift flour and salt together into a bowl.
Cut the cold butter and lard into 1/2-inch slices.
Turn 1/2 of this into flour and cut in with a pastry blender.
Add water and vinegar; blend lightly to make a stiff dough.
Roll out in an oblong; dot it down the center with bits of butter and lard, then fold the left third over center.
Dot this with bits of butter and lard as before, then fold right third over center.
Turn so you have folded edges at top and bottom and roll again.
Repeat until dough has been rolled 3 times, turning each time.
Let rest in cool place for about 30 minutes, then treat as you would any pastry.
This rich and flaky pastry makes a fine topping for deep dish cobblers, meat pies or creamed main dishes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Dip each piece of chicken in mixture of butter or oleo, salt and garlic powder.
Roll in crushed potato chips.
Lay in shallow pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: lemon-orange italian ice
directions: Combine the water and sugar in a medium-sized saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Then boil over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat until cool, then stir in the orange and lemon juices or any other kind of juice.
Pour into a small 10 x 10-inch baking pan.
Cover with foil or plastic wrap and let sit in freezer undisturbed overnight.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in fat until onions are yellow. Add ground beef and fry until beef falls apart.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover last 15 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine dry cake mix, 1/2 cup melted margarine and eggs.
Blend well.
Spread on bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spoon apple pie filling evenly over batter.
In a small bowl, combine brown sugar and cinnamon; cut in 1/4 cup softened margarine and stir in nuts.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Yield: 12 generous servings.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Cream eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Add pumpkin, soda, spices and flour.
Pour into a greased and floured cookie tin.
Add as many chopped nuts on top as you like and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Have a clean towel (dish towel fine) sprinkled with powdered sugar ready.
