As soon as you remove cake from oven, turn onto towel and roll up like a jelly roll.
Let cool completely and unroll; fill with Cream Cheese Filling.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: baked custard
directions: Put milk into one-quart bowl.
Add eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour equal amounts into five (6 ounce) microwave custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Arrange cups in circle in oven.
Cook on Defrost for 9 to 12 minutes.
Remove each custard cup as it begins to bubble or becomes almost set in center.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Serve warm or cold.

title: oktoberfest mustard
directions: Melt butter; whisk in flour.
Cook over medium heat until it bubbles.
Stir in mustard, sugar and milk.
Cook over low heat until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add vinegar; whisk until smooth.
Pour into glass jar and refrigerate.
Good on any kind of sandwich.
Yields 3/4 cup.

title: marshmallow chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour two layer cake pans.
Melt marshmallows over hot water.
Add 1/2 cup hot water and mix until smooth paste; cool.
Add sugar and whip until creamy.
Add sour cream and stir. Fold in flour, soda and salt mixture.
Add beaten eggs. Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until tests done.
Frost as desired.

title: ada's fruit cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time with flour mixture.
Add flavorings, chopped fruits and nuts.
Reserve 1/2 cup flour for fruits and nuts to roll around in to keep from sticking together.
Bake at 250° in loaf pan for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Combine the ingredients; cook over medium heat until bubbly. Stir occasionally.
Cool.
Cover surface with plastic wrap.
After cooled, stir in 1 cup mayonnaise.

title: hello dollie cookies
directions: Layer in 9 x 9-inch pan in order given.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares.

title: hello dollies
directions: Mix melted margarine and crushed graham crackers; spread in the bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Sprinkle with coconut and chopped nuts.
Pour milk on top of preceding.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: 5 a.m. donuts
directions: Heat oil.
Take can of biscuits and open.
Use your fingers to pull apart a hole in middle of biscuit.
Drop in hot oil and turn when brown.
Take out and drain on paper towel.
Mix maple flavor, confectioners sugar and a little milk to make a glaze.
Now, get the riders up for the horse show.

title: edward d. "pop" plumlee's chili
directions: Cook pinto beans until done. In a frying pan, brown ground round, onion and garlic. Add to the pinto beans. Add tomato sauce and seasonings. Salt to taste. Simmer about 2 hours or until it is thick. Serve alone with crackers or with tacos, tamales or hot dogs.

title: french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in tightly covered jar.
Shake well. Store in refrigerator.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving size.
Flour, salt and pepper on one side.
Pound with mallet to tenderize.
Repeat the procedure to the other side.
Brown in oil.
Mix soups and water together. Place meat in casserole.
Pour soup mixture over meat.
Cover; bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: edith's baked potato salad
directions: Toss first 5 ingredients together.
Turn into buttered oblong baking dish.
Top with 1/2 cup partially cooked bacon and 1/4 cup sliced stuffed olives.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yields 12 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Steam cut up, unpeeled zucchini for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cook hamburg with onion, garlic and salt.
Add Ragu sauce.
Layer squash, cheese and hamburg in casserole.
Bake 1/2 hour in a 350° oven.

title: fish stew
directions: Layer onions, potatoes, fish and seasonings until out of fixings.
Add low sodium V-8 juice.
Bring to boil and simmer until done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and dice the apples.
You can use any type of apple that you like, but Cortlands, Gravensteins or Macs will do very well.
Mix and match your apples to get different flavors. Place the apples in a deep 8 x 8 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle the water and lemon juice over the apples.
Cut up the 2 tablespoons of butter and place in among the apples.

title: apple dessert
directions: Melt oleo, then dip out 2 tablespoons and keep for batter. Add apples to oleo and mix well.
Mix in 1/2 cup brown sugar with apples.
I mix it all together in a square baking dish.
Cover with cinnamon well.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients and press in bottom of dish.
Mix next three and spread on pretzels.
Drain juice from pineapple. Mix with sugar and cornstarch and cook until thick.
Cool.
Add pineapple to mixture and spread on cream cheese mixture.

title: refried bean dip
directions: Heat beans with taco seasoning in small saucepan.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Pour beans into pie plate.
Top with sour cream. Spread cheese evenly over top.
Heat in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: coconut kisses
directions: Prepare frosting mix using 1/3 cup boiling water.
Blend thoroughly and beat at high speed until stiff peaks form that bend slightly.
Fold in flour, coconut and almond extract.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Makes approximately 3 1/2 dozen.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Melt butter and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for approximately 3 hours.

title: burrito pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet over medium heat, saute the ground beef for 5 minutes.
Add the onion and garlic, and saute for 5 more minutes.
Drain any excess fat, if desired.
Mix in the olives, green chile peppers, tomatoes with green chile peppers, taco sauce and refried beans.
Stir mixture thoroughly, reduce heat to low, and let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread a thin layer of the meat mixture in the bottom of a 4 quart casserole dish.
Cover with a layer of tortillas followed by more meat mixture, then a layer of cheese.
Repeat tortilla, meat, cheese pattern until all the tortillas are used, topping off with a layer of meat mixture and cheese.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes in the preheated oven, or until cheese is slightly brown and bubbly. Makes 16 servings.

title: sheila's favorite: chicken monterey
directions: Melt butter in skillet over low flame.
Add chicken to skillet. Cook over medium flame (uncovered) approximately 7 to 10 minutes. Add salt and pepper.
Lower flame; add 1 slice of tomato and 1 slice of bell pepper on top of each breast.
Place 2 slices of cheese over tomato and bell pepper on each breast.
Cover skillet until cheese is melted.
Be careful not to overmelt.
Serves four. Great with rice or noodles.
For lemon flavor squeeze lemon before serving.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil Steen's syrup and salt over low heat, stirring constantly. When few drops tested in cold water become brittle, add butter. Pour over the popped corn.
Mix and shape into a large ball.

title: shrimp and tomato skillet
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute peppers and onion.
Stir in rice.
Add water, salt and shrimp.
Bring it to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup.
Heat through, stirring often.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour half the mixture in greased 12 x 15-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes. Melt caramels in butter and milk on stove or microwave, then pour over cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top; pour rest of cake batter on top and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
It's good!

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind all peppers and onion in food processor.
Drain juice. In separate bowl, mix Sure-Jell, sugar and vinegar.
Stir thoroughly and add ground peppers and onions.
Bring to a boil (hard boil).
Once at hard boil, boil 60 seconds.
Remove from heat and stir in 6-ounces Certo.
Skim bubbles and seeds if any.
Ladle into jars to almost top.
Seal or use paraffin seal.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Boil shells; drain.
Brown ground beef with onion and garlic. Take off.
Add egg, bread crumbs and Mozzarella cheese.
Add salt and pepper, if you like. Pour 1/4 cup of Ragu in bottom of baking dish.
Stuff each shell with meat mixture.
Place in baking dish. Pour remaining Ragu over the shells.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
These can be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash and clean cucumbers.
Cut in quarters lengthwise.
Pack in clean jars.
Add 2 heads of dill to each jar and hot peppers, if used.
Mix water, vinegar and salt; bring to boil.
Pour into jars over cucumbers.

title: fiery cajun shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients, except lemon slices and shrimp.
Pour 1/2 cup sauce to cover bottom of baking dish and arrange layers of shrimp and lemon.
Leave 1-inch headroom.
Pour remaining sauce over shrimp.
Bake, uncovered, stirring once, until shrimp are cooked, about 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with French bread and dip shrimp in bread.

title: german kraut salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies. Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter. Combine pudding mix and milk. Put layer of cookies, layer of cream cheese, sugar and butter mixture, then layer of pudding mix and layer of Cool Whip. Repeat layers.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Mix together soups, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and add to the cooked chicken.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with Pam.
Add broccoli; pour chicken mixture over the top.
Top with Ritz crackers and melted butter and bake 1/2 hour to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: holly berry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve.
Should make about 1 gallon.

title: tomato vinaigrette(low-fat)
directions: Blend all ingredients except parsley and onions and store in refrigerator.
In a food processor or by hand, chop fine the parsley and onions.
Add to liquid mixture and you've got yourself a zesty vinaigrette dressing that can also be used to marinate meats and vegetables.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken spinach noodle casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, make white sauce.
Add spinach, onions, celery and rest of seasonings.
Add noodles.
Mix well.
Grease a 3-quart casserole.
Cover the dish with noodles and sauce.
Top with chicken, then grated Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 25 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together and enjoy.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour can of fruit or pie filling in oblong cake pan.
Sprinkle entire package of cake mix (dry) on top.
Do not stir. Cut butter into thin slices and layer over cake mix.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix cookie crumbs with butter in bowl.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumb mixture; press remaining crumbs into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine pudding and milk.
Add cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour over cookie mixture.
Top with remaining crumb mixture; chill.

title: cheese and sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage with onion.
Drain grease.
Add soup, undiluted. Heat until warm.
Serve with chips.

title: best ever barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add other ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: doubly crunchy peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt onto wax paper.
Beat shortening, butter and sugar in medium bowl until smooth.
Beat in egg, vanilla and peanut butter.
Work in dry ingredients until dough is well mixed. Divide dough in half. Wrap each half in plastic wrap. Chill several hours or overnight.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place 3-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Flatten by scoring tops in a crisscross pattern with tines of a fork.
Dip fork each time in cold water to prevent sticking to the dough. Bake cookies at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Transfer at once to wire racks to cool. Store in container with tight fitting lid.

title: crock-pot mexican dip
directions: Combine in crock-pot.
Make sure everything is melted.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in bowl; blend well.
Stir in flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Do not beat.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon into 2 well-greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pistachio dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix with 1 cup of the milk and the vanilla as directed on package, using large mixer bowl.
Add remaining 1 3/4 cups milk and the pie filling mix.
Blend, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Spoon into pie shell.
Chill for at least 4 hours.
Garnish as desired.

title: cottage cheese griddle cakes
directions: Dry the cottage cheese by pressing down in a sieve and let it drain for 1 hour. Beat the eggs well in a mixing bowl.
Add cottage cheese, butter, flour and salt.
Mix only enough to blend.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and pack 1/4-inch deep in a 9 x 13-inch pan or two 7 x 10-inch pans.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Beat the eggs, sugar, flour and lemon juice.
Pour over first ingredients. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
When nearly cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cut while still warm.

title: crock-pot bean medley
directions: Saute onions and sausage.
Drain well.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Place in crock-pot on low and cook.

title: pina coladas
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart freezer-safe bowl, combine limeade, rum and water.
Cover and freeze (mixture does not freeze solid).
Just before serving, place half of mixture in blender.
Cover and blend until slushy.
Repeat with rest.
Pour into cocktail glasses. Serve with 2 short straws.

title: melt-in-your-mouth waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks in small bowl until thick and creamy.
Add milk.
In larger bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold the yolk mixture alternately with flour mixture into egg whites.
Blend.
Pour in melted butter and mix slowly. Put into greased waffle iron.

title: brown sugar coffeecake
directions: Mix flour and brown sugar together.
Set aside 3/4 for topping.
Add egg, buttermilk, soda, salt and cinnamon to remaining flour mixture.
Pour in greased 8 x 8-inch square pan. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: cherry cream cheese coffee cake *
directions: Cut cream cheese and margarine into Bisquick until crumbly. Blend in 1/3 cup milk.
Knead on floured surface.
On wax paper, roll dough into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Turn onto greased baking sheet; remove paper.
Spread preserves down center of dough.
Make 2 1/2-inch cuts at 1-inch intervals on long sides.
Fold strips over filling.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken.
Mix mayonnaise, soup and seasonings and spread over chicken.
Top with cheese and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil; boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; blend together.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: chicken pie
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add flour and cook 3 minutes. Add stock very slowly, stirring constantly.
Season with salt, pepper, paprika and nutmeg.
Add chicken, a small can of drained peas plus carrots, onion and celery (slice about 3 carrots, 1 small onion and a few stalks celery.
Boil until tender, then drain and add to chicken) or can use frozen peas and carrots, boiled with onion and celery.
Pour mixture into deep dish pie plate and top with pie crust.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Boil whole squash until partially done, about 10 minutes.
Cut squash in half lengthwise and scoop out the center of the squash, then chop up the insides and mix with bread crumbs, stuffing mix, onions, salt, pepper, egg, milk and cheese.
Put squash halves in a greased baking dish and fill with dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can top with a slice of cheese if desired.

title: grilled shrimp with vegetable kabobs
directions: Rinse and drain shrimp.
You may choose 1 of 2 methods to prepare the shrimp.
The Good Guy/Gal method is to peel and devein the shrimp, which results in easy dining, but may also result in shrimp that is very dry.
The Rough It method is to leave the shrimp in its shell, which would result in time-consuming dining, but may also result in succulent shrimp.

title: best ever banana nut bread
directions: Measure and sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir until mixed. Stir in bananas.
Fold dry ingredients and nuts into batter.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet bread
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and sugar.
Cut in the shortening.
Add enough buttermilk to make a soft dough. Pinch off dough in pieces the size of a baseball. Shape into biscuits.
Place on greased baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes or until lightly brown and center is done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together with dry jello.
Chill and serve.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, confectioners sugar and margarine.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hungarian stew
directions: Heat fat or oil to smoking hot.
Add onions, stirring until they turn transparent.
Add meat, stirring until just changed to white.
Add paprika.
Cover with water and simmer until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Set out 2 cans tomato sauce.
Measure and set aside 1/4 cup of sauce.
Add remainder to water, vinegar, brown sugar, prepared mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix together and set aside. Combine remaining ingredients and the rest of tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours, basting several times with sauce.

title: festive ham and cheese squares(quick hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Unroll dough into 2 long rectangles.
Place rectangles in 9 x 13 inch baker or baking sheet; press seams together to form crust. Combine butter and mustard; brush on crust.
Sprinkle evenly with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti. Stir butter into hot spaghetti. Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti into a pie crust in a buttered 10-inch pie plate.

title: triple chocolate bundt cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into prepared Bundt cake pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes until cake tests done.
Frost with chocolate glaze or confectioners sugar.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix rice, soups and water together.
Butter 9 x 13-inch oblong baking dish.
Put rice mixture on the bottom.
Place deboned, halved and skinned chicken over mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over chicken breasts.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over chicken.
Cover with heavy foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Don't peek. Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli chicken
directions: In skillet brown chicken in hot oil.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer until done.

title: red cabbage - sweet and sour
directions: Remove damaged outer leaves.
Wash cabbage head under cold running water.
Set on board and cut into quarters.
Remove core and shred finely.
Place in large pot.
Prepare apples and add to pot.
Then water, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 1
hour, stirring frequently.

title: potato salad
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Chill in refrigerator overnight for best flavor.
Can decorate with olive slices and sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: chocolate cherry bundt cake(microwave)
directions: Grease 12-cup microproof Bundt-type pan; chill.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar; shake well to coat.
Mix remaining ingredients except glaze.
Follow cake directions.
Pour into pan.
On cook cycle, cook 18 to 20 minutes.
Rotate overnight every 5 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes.
Drizzle White Cap Glaze over cake.
Let stand until glaze sets.
Serve.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and bring to a hard boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from stove and stir in oats, peanut butter, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and put in dabs on waxed paper.

title: chocolate clusters
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter chips in microwave until soft.
Take out and stir in peanuts or pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on foil or wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: charlie's enchilada pie
directions: Fry hamburger with minced onions until done and then drain. Place a layer of hamburger in bottom of pan (preferably a cast-iron skillet); about 3/4 of an inch thick.
Cover with one can enchilada sauce.
Place two tortillas over meat and pack down firmly.
Place layer of refried beans (about 3/4 of an inch cold out of can) over tortillas, then cover with two more tortillas and pack down firmly.

title: cowboy salad
directions: Mix lettuce, onions, bell pepper, olives and beans.
Just before serving, add Fritos, cheese and dressing.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix ground beef, taco mix and refried beans together.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer all ground beef mixture, then layer of sour cream and last, layer of cheeses.
Bake until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: "grandmom rossi's butter cookies"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine.
Add sugar, eggs, vanilla and baking powder.
Mix thoroughly.
Add four cups of flour and mix.
Now, add remaining two cups and mix.
Bake for ten minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes and boil until tender.
Add onion, margarine, salt and pepper.
Add chicken soup and milk.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: low country boil
directions: Wash, peel and cut potatoes.
Chop onions.
Wash, peel and cut carrots.
Chop sausage into small pieces.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain and combine green beans, yellow beans, kidney beans and chickpeas.
Add pepper and onion.
Combine sugar, oil, salt and pepper.
Add to bean mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: tomato-herb beef short ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In bowl, combine flour, marjoram, rosemary, salt and pepper. Add ribs; toss to coat well in mixture, reserving any that does not cling. In large, deep nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add ribs; cook, turning frequently, until browned on all sides, about 6 minutes. Set aside in roasting pan. To fat in skillet, add carrots, onion and garlic. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is just translucent, about 4 minutes. Stir in wine; cook 1 minute. Stir in tomatoes. Combine broth with reserved flour mixture; stir into carrot mixture. Bring to a boil; cook 1 minute. Pour over ribs in roasting pan. Tightly cover with foil. Roast until meat is tender, about 2 hours. Remove ribs from pan; keep warm on serving platter. Skim fat from pan juices. Serve juices over ribs.

title: mountain pudding
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour batter over melted margarine.
Put pie filling on top of batter.
Bake in oven at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: large pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and shortening; add egg yolks 1 at a time, alternating with flour, beating after each addition. Add flavoring. Dough will be stiff. Beat egg whites, then fold into batter. Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Then bake 1/2 hour at 325°. Reduce heat to 300° and bake 1 more hour. Bake real slow.

title: fresh mushroom soup(low-fat)
directions: Slice caps and stems of mushrooms in thick pieces.
Heat oil in heavy saucepan and saute the mushrooms quickly until just crisp-tender.
Combine all other ingredients in blender and mix until thick and foamy.
Add mushrooms and blend again at lowest speed for 4 or 5 seconds or until mushrooms are chopped into fine pieces but not pulverized.
Pour the mixture back into the saucepan and heat slowly, stirring with a wire whisk to keep from burning.

title: baked stuffed potato
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes.
Bake at 450° for 60 minutes or until potatoes are fully baked.
Cut in half lengthwise and scoop out inside and whip, adding butter, cream, salt and pepper.
Beat egg white until rounded peaks are formed and fold into the potato mixture.
Pile mixture lightly into potato shells, leaving surfaces uneven.
Return to oven 8 to 10 minutes, or until potatoes are thoroughly heated and tops are lightly browned. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken bake
directions: Combine diced, cooked chicken with remaining ingredients (except potato chips) and place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Crush potato chips and put on top of casserole.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes.

title: pear honey
directions: Place pears in food processor until finely chopped but still chunky.
In a 2 to 3-quart microwave casserole, combine all ingredients.
Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Stir well.
Microwave 35 to 40 minutes until pears are translucent and thickened (stir 2 or 3 times).
Pour into 1/2 pint jars.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.
Store in refrigerator up to 1 month.
This has a marmalade texture.

title: apple crisp (for 2)
directions: Place apples in a greased loaf pan.
Mix together all other ingredients and spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream on top.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
When making hot tea, use 2 teaspoons per cup.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt (and optional sugar).
Mix together milk and egg and add fat.
Add milk mixture to cornmeal mixture.
Stir only enough to mix.
Fill greased baking pan half full.
Bake at 425° for about 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: nancy's pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs, 1/3 cup sugar and margarine in bowl. Press on bottom and 2-inches up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan. Set aside.

title: never fail frosting
directions: Combine and cook quickly in iron skillet.
Boil one minute. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Let cool slightly.
Beat until creamy.

title: honey wheat bread(this uses less sugar, salt and fat)
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, 2 cups whole wheat and yeast.
In saucepan, heat milk, water, honey, butter and salt to 120° to 130°.
Add to flour mixture.
Blend on low speed until moistened.
Beat on medium 3 minutes.
Gradually add remaining whole wheat flour and enough of the white flour to form a soft dough.
Turn out and knead 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Place in greased loaf pans.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix
thoroughly and put in jar with tight lid.	Use two teaspoons
per
cup
of hot water (boiling).
More can be used for a stronger drink.

title: mint brownies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool completely.

title: 24-hour fruit salad
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients together until thick; cool.
Add whipped cream, fruit, nuts and marshmallows.
Mix together; let stand overnight.

title: kharkiv cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg and salt until peaks (mix on high).
Gradually blend sugar.
Add chips.
On foil-lined sheet, drop spoonfuls close together.
They don't spread.
Put in oven and turn off.
Take out the next morning.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in granulated sugar.
In another bowl, combine eggs, pumpkin oil, vanilla and brown sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add pie filling; beat 1 minute. Stir in dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.

title: corn dog batter
directions: Coat hot dog with batter and fry in deep fryer.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs
slightly.
Add
sugar,
syrup,
nuts,
salt, vanilla and chopped up butter.
Put into unbaked pie shell and bake about 50 minutes
in oven at 325°.
The pecans will float and form a crust on top if baked slowly.

title: superb pecan pie
directions: Beat sugar into eggs in a medium bowl; beat in corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Stir in pecans; pour into pie shell.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until when a knife inserted midway between center and edge is withdrawn clean, 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool completely on a wire rack.

title: fran's cole slaw
directions: Put cabbage in food processor with blade and chop to desired size.
Repeat until all is chopped.
Repeat with carrots and pepper.
Put in large bowl and add all the remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hancock village chowder
directions: Cook onions in margarine until tender; blend in flour.
Stir in water, potatoes, celery and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: salmon balls
directions: Separate salmon from juice; remove vertabrae. Mix egg into salmon with fork.
In small bowl, combine juice and baking powder; pour into salmon mixture with onions and garlic.
Mix with fork. Add flour.
Drop by teaspoonful into 1/2-inch hot grease in skillet.
Brown each side.
Drain on paper towel and serve hot.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Blend, then mix 2 minutes at medium speed.
Place in tube pan. Bake about 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cake is cool, crumble half of it in bottom of punch bowl.
Mix 1 box pudding as directed on box and pour over cake.
Spread 1/2 pineapple over pudding mixture.
Add 1/2 of cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Add remainder of crumbled cake; spread other box of pudding mixture on cake.
Add remainder of pineapple over pudding; then add remainder of pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip.
Place cherries over top of Cool Whip after they have been drained, then sprinkle nuts on top.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread filling in a 9 x 13 pan. Drain pineapple and sprinkle over filling. Sprinkle cake mix over top. Cut margarine into thin slices and place on top of cake mix. Sprinkle nuts and coconut on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baked broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Chop broccoli, including stems and leaves, into small pieces (about 5 cups). Steam for 10 minutes.

title: hawaiian sweet bread
directions: Set pineapple juice out to warm up to room temperature. Grease three 8 or 9-inch round cake pans.
In a large bowl, combine 3 cups flour, mashed potato flakes, sugar, salt, ginger, vanilla extract and yeast.
In a medium saucepan, heat milk, water and butter until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add warm liquid mixture, pineapple juice and eggs to flour mixture.
Blend mixture at low speed until moistened; beat four minutes at medium speed. By hand, stir in 3 cups of flour to form stiff dough.

title: old world preserves bars
directions: In a large bowl combine first 5 ingredients.
Beat on low speed until mix is crumbly, 2 to 3 minutes.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of mix.
Press remaining mix on bottom of a greased 9-inch pan. Spread preserves to 1/2 inch of edges.
Crumble reserved mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Mix nectar and cake mix together.
Add the eggs, oil and bake in loaf pan for 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: venison steak
directions: Cut steaks from the leg half an inch thick; broil about 5 minutes.
Season with salt, pepper and butter.
Make a gravy of a cup of water and half a cup of currant jelly.
Thicken with flour and butter; boil once and turn over the steak.
Serve hot.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine ingredients, folding in the stiffly beaten egg whites last.
Place mixture in well-greased pans and bake in hot oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into floured and greased pan. Cook slowly on lower heat until well done.

title: zucchini stuffed with tomatoes
directions: Place whole zucchini in a medium saucepan with boiling salted water. Cook 10 minutes or until tender. Drain well. Cut zucchini in half lengthwise; remove and reserve pulp for other uses, leaving a firm shell. Sprinkle each shell cavity with salt and pepper; set aside. Melt butter in a medium saucepan. Add croutons, and toss gently. Combine buttered croutons with tomatoes. Mix well. Place zucchini shells in a lightly greased shallow baking dish; spoon tomato mixture into shells. Cover and bake at 450° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese; bake, uncovered, an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: cream of wheat dumplings
directions: Bring milk and salt to a boil in saucepan.
Add Cream of Wheat. Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and beat in butter and eggs until well mixed.
Stir in parsley.
Drop by spoonfuls into soup.
Simmer, covered, for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: 20-minute chicken parmesan
directions: Flatten chicken to even thickness.
Dip chicken into egg, then into crumbs to coat.
Brown chicken in hot margarine, in skillet over medium heat.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and baking powder. Add pumpkin, oil, eggs, nuts, and raisins. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened and mixture is smooth. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: honey-bun cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and sour cream. Mix for 3 minutes. Pour 1/2 mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle onto 1/2 mixture. Pour rest of batter on top. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes until done. Punch holes in cake and pour the following mixture onto cake.

title: snow logs or sand tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small logs or half-moon shapes.
Bake in slow oven and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: rhubarb sherbet
directions: Wash rhubarb and cut into 1-inch pieces (approximately 6 cups). Combine rhubarb, sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil, then cover and cook over low heat until soft, approximately 10 minutes.
Cool to lukewarm.
Puree cooled mixture in blender. Stir in corn syrup and pour into 3 ice cube trays.
Freeze until hard around edges but soft in center. Put frozen cubes in mixer bowl and mix quickly.
Whip cream until stiff.
Fold into rhubarb mix.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Fold into rhubarb mix.
Add food coloring to mix to turn it pink.
Return mix to freezer and chill until firm.
Serve and enjoy!

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
May be refrigerated overnight.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients for cake and bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from oven and cover with miniature marshmallows.
Put back in oven to melt.
